body":"## Source repository\n\n- Repo: https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum\n- Branch: `main`\n- Verified SHA: `c853e44ffce77b771069b6df6bd5adc1b78f1b2f`\n- Verification: `git ls-remote --symref https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum HEAD`\n\n## Language extractor\n\n- Primary language: Rust (extension: `.rs`)\n\n## Framework idioms exercised\n\nRouter::new().route(), extractors (Path, Query, Json, State), tower middleware layers, async handler fns (examples/ dir extensive)\n\n## Acceptance\n\n- [ ] Repo cloned at the verified SHA into VERIFY-2 corpus fixtures\n- [ ] Indexer extracts routes/controllers/handlers from the sample\n- [ ] No regressions in existing corpus\n\nforbidden-term grep: clean\n\nRefs #87\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/268/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/cajasmota/archigraph/issues/268/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741/events","html_url":"https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741","id":4366328051,"node_id":"I_kwDOFi7l3s8AAAABBEDg8w","number":3741,"title":"Handling of HEAD requests violates RFC 9110","user":{"login":"lorenzleutgeb","id":542154,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU0MjE1NA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/542154?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb","html_url":"https://github.com/lorenzleutgeb","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":3217112532,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwzMjE3MTEyNTMy","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/labels/C-bug","name":"C-bug","color":"f5f1fd","default":false,"description":"Category: This is a bug."},{"id":3548183885,"node_id":"LA_kwDOFi7l3s7TfP1N","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/labels/A-axum","name":"A-axum","color":"ffdc1c","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":21,"created_at":"2026-05-01T19:42:21Z","updated_at":"2026-05-15T14:56:24Z","closed_at":"2026-05-15T14:56:24Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Bug Report\n\nAxum responds to HEAD requests with `content-length: 0`, which (in almost all cases) violates HTTP semantics. Refer to [RFC 9110, Sec. 9.3.2, Paragraph 2](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9110#section-9.3.2-2).\n\nIf the value for the `content-length` header that would be produced in response to a GET request is not known at the time of responding to a HEAD request, then it should be omitted, not included with a value of 0.\n\nReal-world example: A handler that archives data into a `*.zip` file and responds with the archive. Assume that there is quite a lot of data, so archiving just to know the length of the hypothetical response to GET would be considered wasteful. It would be incorrect to respond with `content-length: 0`, because the archive itself will likely not be the empty file.\n\nThe same argument is used in https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/pull/755#issuecomment-1037931480, so I allow myself to mention the author: @davidpdrsn\n\nPrevious issues that seem to be related:\n - https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/730\n - https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/747\n\n### Version\n\nChecked out https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum.git at commit `9f4d52e310a6053e49f3db09ce02f723a7a3f5bb` which is `main` as of 2026-05-01.\n\n### Platform\n\nNixOS on Windows Subsystem for Linux, likely irrelevant.\n\n```\nLinux wsl 6.6.87.2-microsoft-standard-WSL2 #1 SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Thu Jun  5 18:30:46 UTC 2025 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n```\n\n### Description\n\nI tried this code: https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/blob/9f4d52e310a6053e49f3db09ce02f723a7a3f5bb/examples/handle-head-request/src/main.rs\n\nActual:\n\n```shell-session\n$ git clone https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum.git\n$ cd axum/example/handle-head-request\n$ cargo run -p example-handle-head-request\n[build output]\nlistening on 127.0.0.1:3000\n$ curl -s -D - -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:3000/get-head\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\ncontent-type: text/plain; charset=utf-8\nx-some-header: header from GET\ncontent-length: 13\ndate: [current date and time]\n$ curl -s -D - -o /dev/null --head http://127.0.0.1:3000/get-head\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\nx-some-header: header from HEAD\ncontent-length: 0\ndate: [current date and time]\n```\n\nExpected:\n\n```diff\n $ git clone https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum.git\n $ cd axum/example/handle-head-request\n $ cargo run -p example-handle-head-request\n [build output]\n listening on 127.0.0.1:3000\n $ curl -s -D - -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:3000/get-head\n HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n content-type: text/plain; charset=utf-8\n x-some-header: header from GET\n content-length: 13\n date: [current date and time]\n $ curl -s -D - -o /dev/null --head http://127.0.0.1:3000/get-head\n HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n x-some-header: header from HEAD\n-content-length: 0\n date: [current date and time]\n```\n\nAlternative Resolution (more complicated to implement):\n\n```diff\n $ git clone https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum.git\n $ cd axum/example/handle-head-request\n $ cargo run -p example-handle-head-request\n [build output]\n listening on 127.0.0.1:3000\n $ curl -s -D - -o /dev/null http://127.0.0.1:3000/get-head\n HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n content-type: text/plain; charset=utf-8\n x-some-header: header from GET\n content-length: 13\n date: [current date and time]\n $ curl -s -D - -o /dev/null --head http://127.0.0.1:3000/get-head\n HTTP/1.1 200 OK\n x-some-header: header from HEAD\n-content-length: 0\n+content-length: 13\n date: [current date and time]\n```\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13/events","html_url":"https://github.com/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13","id":4490695142,"node_id":"I_kwDOSjaUgM8AAAABC6qR5g","number":13,"title":"[antigravity] WBS-9.1b: svdc-console crate scaffold + rust-embed wiring","user":{"login":"yongalee","id":16199520,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2MTk5NTIw","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubuserconten