king":0},"body":"## WBS code\nWBS-9.1b — svdc-console crate scaffold\n\n## Commands to run\n```bash\n# Create new crate\nmkdir -p crates/svdc-console/src/{routes,sse,templates,assets}\n# Author Cargo.toml with deps per ADR-0004: axum, tokio (rt-multi-thread, macros),\n# maud, rust-embed, serde, serde_json, tower-http (CompressionLayer optional)\n# Author minimal src/lib.rs exporting pub fn router() -> axum::Router\n# Add to workspace members in root Cargo.toml\ncargo build -p svdc-console\n```\n\n## Expected output / acceptance criteria\n- `crates/svdc-console/Cargo.toml` exists with the deps listed in ADR-0004\n- `crates/svdc-console/src/lib.rs` exposes `pub fn router() -> axum::Router` returning an empty router that responds 200 OK on `GET /`\n- Root `Cargo.toml` workspace `members` includes `crates/svdc-console`\n- `cargo build --workspace` passes\n- `cargo clippy --workspace --all-targets -- -D warnings` passes\n- Initial unit test asserts the router builds without panic\n\n## Branch name to use\nantigravity/wbs-9-1b-crate-scaffold\n\n## Files / crates in scope\n- `crates/svdc-console/` (new)\n- `Cargo.toml` (workspace members)\n\n## Pre-flight (per AGENTS.md)\n- [x] Antigravity-appropriate (new crate scaffold after design settled per ADR-0004).\n- [x] No prior ADR contradicted; ADR-0004 governs.\n- [x] Will stop and open for:claude if a non-ADR-listed dep is required.\n\n## Reference\n- Handoff plan: https://github.com/yongalee/SVDC/blob/main/docs/dual-agent/wbs-9-ui-handoff.md\n- Stack ADR: docs/decisions/0004-ui-stack.md\n- Toggle ADR: docs/decisions/0005-daemon-vs-ui-mode.md\n\nThis unblocks #15 (CI matrix), #16 (9.1a base layout), and downstream WBS-9 work.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/yongalee/SVDC/issues/13/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287","id":4491795288,"node_id":"I_kwDOKKxnMM8AAAABC7tbWA","number":287,"title":"bug(shared-transport-services): outer shutdown_signal race cancels inner graceful shutdown","user":{"login":"ivonnyssen","id":1139418,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjExMzk0MTg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1139418?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen","html_url":"https://github.com/ivonnyssen","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ivonnyssen/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":5879960712,"node_id":"LA_kwDOKKxnMM8AAAABXnkUiA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/labels/bug","name":"bug","color":"d73a4a","default":true,"description":"Something isn't working"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-21T04:40:58Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T18:15:07Z","closed_at":"2026-05-23T18:15:07Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Problem\n\nEvery shared-transport ASCOM service's `main.rs` races `bound.start()` against a *second* `shutdown_signal()` in an outer `tokio::select!`. When the signal branch wins, `bound.start()` is dropped mid-flight — which means the **inner** `with_graceful_shutdown` future inside `rp_tls::server::serve_plain` / `serve_tls` never gets a chance to flush in-flight requests or drain connections cleanly. The driver exits as soon as the outer `select!` resolves.\n\n## Affected services\n\nAll five shared-transport ASCOM services have a verbatim copy of the same pattern:\n\n| Service | `main.rs` lines | `lib.rs` graceful shutdown |\n|---|---|---|\n| `dsd-fp2` | `main.rs:117-120` | `lib.rs:154,160` |\n| `qhy-focuser` | `main.rs:119-121` | `lib.rs:159,165` |\n| `ppba-driver` | `main.rs:158-161` | `lib.rs:160,166` |\n| `pa-falcon-rotator` | `main.rs:121-123` | `lib.rs:177,183` |\n| `star-adventurer-gti` | `main.rs:146-148` | `lib.rs:209,215` |\n\nThe shape in `main.rs` (using `dsd-fp2` as the example — others are identical except for log messages):\n\n```rust\ntokio::select! {\n    result = bound.start() => { result?; }\n    () = shutdown_signal() => { info!(\\\"Shutting down\\\"); }\n}\n```\n\nThe shape in `lib.rs::BoundServer::start`:\n\n```rust\n// serves with axum's with_graceful_shutdown wired to its own shutdown_signal()\nrp_tls::server::serve_plain(self.listener, self.router, shutdown_signal()).await?;\n```\n\n## Why it matters\n\n- **Graceful shutdown is silently bypassed.** Axum's `with_graceful_shutdown` waits for active connections to finish; that work never runs when the outer `select!` drops `bound.start()`.\n- **Spurious connection-aborted log lines** observed by clients during normal SIGTERM.\n- **Coverage tools** (llvm-cov profraw flush in `ppba-driver`'s comment) can lose data if `Drop` impls don't run promptly.\n\nEach service's `shutdown_signal()` is a private duplicate of the same `ctrl_c` + SIGTERM `select!` — so the outer one in `main.rs` and the inner one in `lib.rs` install **two** independent signal handlers that listen for the same signal. Whichever future tokio polls first wins, and the loser is dropped.\n\n## Suggested fix\n\nPick one of these (in order of preference):\n\n1. **Drop the outer `select!` entirely.** Just `bound.start().await?;` — the inner graceful shutdown already covers Ctrl-C/SIGTERM. Delete the per-service `shutdown_signal()` in `main.rs` (the one in `lib.rs` stays). Simplest, but loses the `info!(\\\"Shutting down\\\")` log line — could move that into the inner shutdown future or the BoundServer.\n\n2. **Pass a shutdown future into `bound.start()`.** Add an optional `shutdown_signal: impl Future<Output=()>` parameter to `BoundServer::start` (or a `start_with_shutdown` variant). `main.rs` constructs the signal future and passes it in; `lib.rs` plumbs it down to `serve_plain`/`serve_tls` so axum's `with_graceful_shutdown` sees the same future. One signal installation, deterministic shutdown path.\n\n3. **Use a `CancellationToken` shared between main and the server.** `main.rs` spawns a task that triggers the token on signal; `bound.start()` accepts an `&CancellationToken` and forwards to axum. Most flexible if other shutdown sources need to plug in later (e.g., admin endpoint, watchdog).\n\nRecommend (2) — minimal API change, gives `main.rs` somewhere to put the `info!` log, and works the same for both `serve_plain` and `serve_tls` paths.\n\n## Scope\n\nTouches:\n- `main.rs` in all five services (drop or restructure the outer `select!`)\n- `lib.rs::BoundServer::start` signature in all five services\n- Possibly `rp-tls`'s `serve_plain` / `serve_tls` signatures if option (2) needs a callable shutdown future passed through\n\nShould be a single PR — the pattern is identical across services, so the diff is mechanical once one service is converted.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- All five services have one (not two) shutdown signal installation\n- A SIGTERM during an in-flight ASCOM request waits for the request to finish (or hit its server-side timeout) before the process exits\n- The `info!(\\\"Shutting down\\\")` log line still fires once per shutdown\n- No regressions in existing SIGTERM tests (`services/*/tests/test_lib.rs` shutdown coverage)\n\n## Source\n\nSpotted by Copilot on PR #283 (https://github.com/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/pull/283#discussion_r3278273804). Deferred from that PR because the fix should be uniform across services, not dsd-fp2-specific.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ivonnyssen/rusty-photon/issues/287/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158/events","html_url":"https://github.com/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158","id":4344462246,"node_id":"I_kwDOPbiLaM8AAAABAvM7pg","number":158,"title":"test(websocket): add wire-level WebSocket integration test infrastructure — current tests never perform protocol handshake","user":{"login":"bug-ops","id":12019904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDE5OTA0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12019904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops","html_url":"https://github.com/bug-ops","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":9087382129,"node_id":"LA_kwDOPbiLaM8AAAACHaZycQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"a2eeef","default":true,"description":"New feature or request"},{"id":10058041296,"node_id":"LA_kwDOPbiLaM8AAAACV4GH0A","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/labels/core","name":"core","color":"0075ca","default":false,"description":"Changes to pjs-core crate"},{"id":10058042452,"node_id":"LA_kwDOPbiLaM8AAAACV4GMVA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/labels/testing","name":"testing","color":"bfd4f2","default":false,"description":"Test coverage improvements, new test cases"},{"id":10811883496,"node_id":"LA_kwDOPbiLaM8AAAAChHA_6A","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/labels/P2","name":"P2","color":"e4e669","default":false,"description":"Medium priority — suboptimal behavior, API inconsistency"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[{"login":"bug-ops","id":12019904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDE5OTA0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12019904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops","html_url":"https://github.com/bug-ops","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false}],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-28T15:48:38Z","updated_at":"2026-04-28T16:14:35Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T16:14:35Z","assignee":{"login":"bug-ops","id":12019904,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyMDE5OTA0","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/12019904?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops","html_url":"https://github.com/bug-ops","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/bug-ops/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Description\n\nThe existing WebSocket test suite (`websocket_server_comprehensive.rs`, `websocket_security.rs`) tests only struct-level methods on `AxumWebSocketTransport`. It never performs a WebSocket protocol upgrade, exchanges frames over the wire, or verifies that `WsMessage` payloads are received by a connected client.\n\nThis is why multiple WebSocket transport defects (#122, and the now-closed #147 and #149) were undetected by automated tests and were only caught during manual live testing. There is no infrastructure to write integration tests that:\n1. Bind the axum router on a real port\n2. Open a WebSocket connection via `tokio-tungstenite`\n3. Send structured `WsMessage` payloads (JSON text frames)\n4. Assert on received frames\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n\n1. Run `cargo nextest run --all-features -p pjson-rs` — all WebSocket tests pass\n2. Manually connect to the demo server via `ws://localhost:3001/ws/{session_id}`\n3. Send a `StreamInit` message — observe that no frames are delivered (issue #149)\n4. Observe: the passing tests give false confidence\n\n## Expected Behavior\n\nIntegration tests verify the full WebSocket protocol stack: upgrade handshake → frame exchange → connection close. Regressions in `send_frame()`, `StreamInit`, or `close_stream()` are caught in CI.\n\n## Actual Behavior\n\nZero wire-level WebSocket tests exist. All tests exercise the transport struct via trait methods that internally discard messages silently.\n\n## Environment\n\n- Version: v0.5.1 (HEAD: 135b8ee)\n- Features: http-server, websocket-server\n- Existing tests: `crates/pjs-core/tests/websocket_server_comprehensive.rs`\n\n## Implementation Sketch\n\n`tokio-tungstenite` is already a workspace dependency (`websocket-client` feature). The pattern is:\n\n```rust\nasync fn spawn_test_server() -> std::net::SocketAddr {\n    let listener = tokio::net::TcpListener::bind(\"127.0.0.1:0\").await.unwrap();\n    let addr = listener.local_addr().unwrap();\n    tokio::spawn(async move {\n        axum::serve(listener, build_test_router()).await.unwrap();\n    });\n    addr\n}\n\n#[tokio::test]\nasync fn test_ws_stream_init_delivers_frames() {\n    let addr = spawn_test_server().await;\n    let (mut ws, _) = connect_async(format!(\"ws://{addr}/pjs/ws/test\")).await.unwrap();\n    ws.send(Message::Text(serde_json::to_string(&WsMessage::StreamInit { ... }).unwrap())).await.unwrap();\n    let frame = timeout(Duration::from_secs(5), ws.next()).await\n        .expect(\"timeout waiting for frame\").unwrap().unwrap();\n    assert!(matches!(frame, Message::Text(_)));\n}\n```\n\nAlternatively, `axum-test` v18 (`features = [\"ws\"]`) provides `TestServer::get_websocket()` without manual port binding — worth evaluating.\n\n## See Also\n\n- Issues #122 (close_stream no-op), #147 (send_frame discards, closed), #149 (StreamInit no streaming, closed)\n- Official axum WebSocket testing example: https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/blob/main/examples/testing-websockets/src/main.rs\n- `axum-test` crate with WebSocket support: https://docs.rs/axum-test\n\n## Spec\n\n.local/specs/012-websocket-integration-test-infra/spec.md","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/bug-ops/pjs/issues/158/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14651","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14651/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14651/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14651/events","html_url":"https://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14651","id":4401710204,"node_id":"I_kwDOGBlvNc8AAAABBlzEfA","number":14651,"title":"bug(`anvil`): `eth_sendTransaction` panics on OP deposit tx with `mint` > u128::MAX","user":{"log