ime::task::raw::poll::hea92165a86f27106\n      at <unknown source file>:<unknown line>\n  28: std::sys::backtrace::__rust_begin_short_backtrace::h9c3862060137f44f\n      at <unknown source file>:<unknown line>\n  29: core::ops::function::FnOnce::call_once{{vtable.shim}}::hcfe9b68333e25a74\n      at <unknown source file>:<unknown line>\n  30: <std[e28293b1aa0f68bd]::sys::thread::unix::Thread>::new::thread_start<unknown>\n      at <unknown source file>:<unknown line>\n\nRun with COLORBT_SHOW_HIDDEN=1 environment variable to disable frame filtering.\nRun with RUST_BACKTRACE=full to include source snippets.\nAborted                    (core dumped) anvil\n```\n\n### Reproduce\n\nStart anvil:\n```bash\nanvil\n```\n\nSend `eth_feeHistory` with a `blockCount` greater than `u64::MAX`:\n```bash\ncurl -s -X POST -H 'Content-Type: application/json' --data '{\n  \"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":1,\"method\":\"eth_feeHistory\",\"params\":[\"0x010000000000000000\",\"latest\",[]]\n}' http://127.0.0.1:8545\n```\n\n### Cause\n\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/5581adf9041cc4df777de01d6867c070500fe712/crates/anvil/src/eth/api.rs#L1129\n\n`U256::to::<u64>()` panics on overflow. The `.min(MAX_BLOCK_COUNT)` clamp runs *after* the cast and can't prevent it.\n\n### Fix\n\nReplace the panicking conversion with a saturating one:\n\n```rust\nlet block_count = block_count.saturating_to::<u64>().min(MAX_BLOCK_COUNT);\n```","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14653/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/foundry-rs/foundry/issues/14653/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59/events","html_url":"https://github.com/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59","id":4444047478,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ4lOWc8AAAABCOLIdg","number":59,"title":"Upgrade ailoop-server to Axum 0.8 (Newton embed compatibility)","user":{"login":"aroff","id":4482374,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0ODIzNzQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4482374?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff","html_url":"https://github.com/aroff","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-14T07:23:43Z","updated_at":"2026-05-14T11:38:26Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T11:38:26Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"---\nissue: 59\nbranch: feature/59-upgrade-ailoop-server-to-axum-0-8-newton-embed-compatibility\nboard_item_id: PVTI_lADODzJpH84BRFoCzgstE_0\nsource: github-project\n---\n\n# Spec 59 — Upgrade `ailoop-server` to Axum 0.8 (Newton Embed Compatibility)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\n`ailoop-server` currently depends on **Axum 0.7**, **Tower 0.4**, and **tower-http 0.5** declared in the workspace root `Cargo.toml`. The downstream consumer **gonewton/newton** pins **Axum 0.8** in its own workspace. Because `axum::Router` is a concrete type whose identity is tied to its crate version, an Axum 0.7 `Router` returned by `ailoop_server::router()` cannot be merged or nested inside an Axum 0.8 application — the compiler rejects the type mismatch. This blocks Newton from embedding `ailoop_server::router()` into `newton serve` on a single listener.\n\nThe fix is a targeted version bump of the three HTTP-stack crates (`axum`, `tower`, `tower-http`) across the workspace, followed by the compile-error fixes that Axum 0.8's breaking API changes introduce in `ailoop-server/src/`. No logic changes are intended.\n\n**Out of scope:** aligning `reqwest` 0.11 across the workspace (tracked as a separate nice-to-have); any Newton-side changes to merge the router; changes to `ailoop-core` or `ailoop-py`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Goals\n\n1. The workspace `Cargo.toml` declares `axum = \"0.8\"`, `tower = \"0.5\"`, and `tower-http = \"0.6\"`.\n2. `cargo build --workspace` succeeds with no errors or warnings introduced by this change.\n3. `cargo test --workspace` (all affected crates) passes.\n4. The public embed API — `router()`, `spawn_background_tasks()`, `AiloopAppState`, `ServeConfig`, `AuthConfig`, `CorsConfig`, `AiloopError` — remains callable from an Axum 0.8 embedder without changes to the call sites' semantic intent (signature adaptations are acceptable and MUST be documented in `CHANGELOG.md`).\n5. `CHANGELOG.md` records the Axum major version bump for downstream library embedders.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Current Behavior\n\n### Component table\n\n| Component | Role | Mutable at runtime? |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Cargo.toml` (workspace root) | Declares `axum = \"0.7\"`, `tower = \"0.4\"`, `tower-http = \"0.5\"` | No — compile-time |\n| `ailoop-server/Cargo.toml` | Inherits `axum`, `tower`, `tower-http` from workspace; declares `reqwest = \"0.11\"` directly | No |\n| `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml` | Inherits `axum` from workspace; no direct tower/tower-http deps | No |\n| `ailoop-server/src/server/core.rs` | Constructs `axum::Router`, calls `axum::serve`, handles WebSocket upgrades | No (build artifact) |\n| `ailoop-server/src/middleware/auth.rs` | Implements `tower::{Layer, Service}` manually for auth middleware | No |\n| `ailoop-server/src/server/api.rs` | Defines REST route handlers using `axum::extract::State`, response types | No |\n\n**Current build flow:** `cargo build --workspace` resolves `axum 0.7.x`, `tower 0.4.x`, `tower-http 0.5.x`. `ailoop-cli` also pulls `axum` from the workspace. The `ailoop-server` library compiles as a crate exposing `router()` which returns `axum::Router` (Axum 0.7 type).\n\n**Current resume / start flow:** `AiloopServer::start_with_shutdown()` calls `router()` → binds a `TcpListener` → calls `axum::serve(listener, built_router.into_make_service()).with_graceful_shutdown(shutdown_future).await`. The `router()` function uses `axum::Router::new()`, `.route()`, `.merge()`, `.fallback()`, `.with_state()`, `.nest()`, and layer composition (`AuthLayer`, `CorsLayer`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Design\n\n### 4.1 Version bump strategy\n\nThe three crates MUST be updated in `[workspace.dependencies]` only; individual crate `Cargo.toml` files inherit them via `{ workspace = true }` and require no version edits. The target versions are:\n\n```toml\n# Cargo.toml (workspace root) — [workspace.dependencies]\naxum          = { version = \"0.8\", features = [\"ws\"] }\ntower         = \"0.5\"\ntower-http    = { version = \"0.6\", features = [\"trace\", \"cors\"] }\n```\n\n`reqwest = \"0.11\"` in `ailoop-server/Cargo.toml` is **not touched** (out of scope).\n\n### 4.2 Axum 0.8 API surface changes requiring code fixes\n\nThe following Axum 0.7 → 0.8 breaking changes affect this codebase and MUST be resolved:\n\n| Area | Axum 0.7 usage (current) | Axum 0.8 required form |\n|---|---|---|\n| `axum::serve` | `axum::serve(listener, router.into_make_service())` | `axum::serve(listener, router)` — `into_make_service()` call removed (Router now implements `IntoMakeService` directly via blanket impl, or `axum::serve` accepts `Router` directly) |\n| WebSocket text frame | `WsMessage::Text(t)` where `t: String` — pattern match on `Text(t)` | Unchanged in intent; verify no type annotation changes needed for `t` |\n| Nesting comment in `core.rs` | Comment references `axum 0.7` nesting behavior at line 1166 | Comment MUST be updated to reference Axum 0.8 nesting semantics |\n| `axum::body::Body` in `auth.rs` | `use axum::{body::Body, ...}` used as `Request<Body>` | Confirm `axum::body::Body` is still the canonical body type; update import path if moved |\n| `tower-http` CORS layer | `tower_http::cors::CorsLayer` API (0.5) | Verify `CorsLayer::new()`, `.allow_origin()`, `.allow_credentials()` method names against 0.6 changelog; update if renamed |\n\n### 4.3 Tower 0.5 API surface changes in `auth.rs`\n\n`ailoop-server/src/middleware/auth.rs` manually implements `tower::{Layer, Service}`. Tower 0.5 changes that MUST be checked and fixed:\n\n- `Service::call` signature: still `fn call(&mut self, req: Request<Body>) -> Self::Future` — unchanged.\n- `Service::poll_ready` signature: still `fn poll_ready(&mut self, cx: &mut Context<'_>) -> Poll<Result<(), Self::Error>>` — unchanged.\n- `Layer::layer` signature: unchanged.\n- Verify `tower::Service` and `tower::Layer` import paths are identical in 0.5.\n\n### 4.4 Concurrency and state model\n\nNo changes to the concurrency or state model. `AiloopAppState` remains an `Arc<T>`-composed struct. The `CancellationToken` lifecycle is unchanged. This spec introduces no new async primitives.\n\n### 4.5 Invariants\n\n- `router()` MUST remain a pure, non-I/O factory function returning `Result<axum::Router, AiloopError>`.\n- `spawn_background_tasks()` MUST continue to accept a `CancellationToken` parameter.\n- The nesting rule (`base_path` trailing-slash handling) MUST preserve the same observable routing behavior under Axum 0.8.\n\n### 4.6 Collision and error conditions\n\nNo new error conditions introduced. Existing `AiloopError` variants are sufficient. Compilation failures from API mismatches are resolved in Stage 2 before any merge.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Schema and API\n\nThe public embed API surface is **unchanged in intent**. Any signature adaptation (e.g., removal of `.into_make_service()` at the call site inside `start_with_shutdown`) is internal. The exported symbols below MUST remain public and callable from an Axum 0.8 embedder:\n\n```rust\n// ailoop-server/src/lib.rs — public exports (unchanged)\npub use crate::config::{AuthConfig, CorsConfig, ServeConfig};\npub use crate::error::AiloopError;\npub use crate::server::core::{router, spawn_background_tasks};\npub use crate::state::AiloopAppState;\npub use server::AiloopServer;\npub use server::ServerStatus;\n\n// router() signature — may change only in return type if axum::Router internals require it\npub fn router(\n    state: Arc<AiloopAppState>,\n    config: &ServeConfig,\n) -> Result<axum::Router, AiloopError>;\n\n// spawn_background_tasks() signature — unchanged\npub fn spawn_background_tasks(\n    state: Arc<AiloopAppState>,\n    config: &ServeConfig,\n    token: tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken,\n) -> tokio::task::JoinHandle<()>;\n```\n\nStructs that MUST remain constructible by embedders:\n\n```rust\npub struct ServeConfig {\n    pub host: String,\n    pub port: u16,\n    pub default_channel: String,\n    pub base_path: Option<String>,\n    pub web: bool,\n    pub auth: Option<AuthConfig>,\n    pub cors: Option<CorsConfig>,\n}\n\npub struct AuthConfig {\n    pub tokens: Vec<String>,\n}\n\npub struct CorsConfig {\n    pub allowed_origins: Vec<String>,\n    pub allow_credentials: bool,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone)]\npub struct AiloopAppState {\n    pub channel_manager: Arc<ChannelIsolation>,\n    pub message_history: Arc<MessageHistory>,\n    pub broadcast_manager: Arc<BroadcastManager>,\n    pub task_storage: Arc<TaskStorage>,\n    pub pending_prompt_registry: Arc<PendingPromptRegistry>,\n    pub default_channel: String,\n    pub web: bool,\n    // pub(crate) fields omitted from embed surface\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Error Codes\n\nThis spec introduces no new error codes. All existing `AiloopError` variants are preserved:\n\n| Code (variant) | Category | Trigger |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AiloopError::InvalidBasePath(String)` | Config validation | `base_path` fails format rules in `normalized_base_path()` |\n| `AiloopError::ServerShuttingDown` | Lifecycle | Request arrives after cancellation token is cancelled |\n| `AiloopError::Unauthorized` | Auth | Token absent or not in `AuthConfig::tokens` |\n| `AiloopError::AddressParse(AddrParseError)` | Config | `host:port` string cannot be parsed as `SocketAddr` |\n| `AiloopError::Io(io::Error)` | Runtime | Underlying I/O failure (bind, accept, etc.) |\n| `AiloopError::Internal(String)` | Runtime | Any other internal invariant violation |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. `cargo build --workspace` on the updated branch exits with code 0 and no new compiler errors or warnings attributable to this change.\n2. `cargo test --workspace` exits with code 0 for all test cases across `ailoop-core`, `ailoop-server`, and `ailoop-cli`.\n3. `ailoop-server/Cargo.toml` does not declare an explicit `axum` version — it inherits `axum = \"0.8\"` from the workspace.\n4. `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml` does not declare an explicit `axum` version — it inherits `axum = \"0.8\"` from the workspace.\n5. `Cargo.lock` (post-update) contains no `axum 0.7.x` entry.\n6. `Cargo.lock` (post-update) contains no `tower 0.4.x` entry.\n7. `Cargo.lock` (post-update) contains no `tower-http 0.5.x` entry.\n8. An embedder crate that declares `axum = \"0.8\"` and calls `ailoop_server::router(state, &config)` compiles without type-mismatch errors.\n9. `CHANGELOG.md` contains a new section documenting the Axum 0.8 / Tower 0.5 / tower-http 0.6 bump and any signature changes for embedders.\n10. `router()` remains a pure factory (no I/O side effects) returning `Result<axum::Router, AiloopError>` — verified by reading the implementation post-merge.\n11. The `auth` feature compile path (`#[cfg(feature = \"auth\")]`) continues to compile correctly with Tower 0.5 `Layer` and `Service` traits.\n12. The `web-ui` feature compile path (`#[cfg(feature = \"web-ui\")]`) continues to compile correctly under Axum 0.8.\n13. `AiloopError::InvalidBasePath` is still returned (not panicked) when `base_path = \"/api\"` is passed to `router()` — existing behavior is not regressed.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Functionality Comparison (Before vs After)\n\n| Capability | Before (Axum 0.7) | After (Axum 0.8) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Router construction | `axum::Router` (0.7 type) | `axum::Router` (0.8 type) — same API, same semantics |\n| Serving | `router.into_make_service()` passed to `axum::serve` | `router` passed directly (or adapted per Axum 0.8 `serve` signature) |\n| Auth middleware | `tower::{Layer, Service}` (tower 0.4) | `tower::{Layer, Service}` (tower 0.5) — same trait shape |\n| CORS layer | `tower_http::cors::CorsLayer` (0.5) | `tower_http::cors::CorsLayer` (0.6) — API confirmed for compatibility |\n| Embed compatibility | Newton (Axum 0.8) cannot embed `router()` | Newton can merge/nest the returned `Router` directly |\n| WebSocket handling | `axum::extract::ws::WebSocketUpgrade` (0.7) | `axum::extract::ws::WebSocketUpgrade` (0.8) |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Benefit of Implementing This Functionality\n\n**Primary:** Unblocks Newton from embedding `ailoop_server::router()` into `newton serve`, eliminating the need to run ailoop as a separate process for HIL (human-in-the-loop) functionality. This reduces operational complexity and latency for Newton deployments.\n\n**Secondary:** Aligns the ailoop workspace with the current Axum ecosystem, reducing dependency divergence over time and making it easier to pull in future Axum improvements.\n\n**Risk if skipped:** Newton must maintain a proxy/sidecar architecture indefinitely, adding a network hop and deployment complexity. Future Axum ecosystem libraries (e.g., axum-extra, axum-login) published for 0.8 will be inaccessible to ailoop-server's direct dependents.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Stages\n\n### Stage 1 — Workspace dependency bump\n\n**Deliverable:** Updated `Cargo.toml` workspace file with new versions; `cargo fetch` succeeds.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Edit `[workspace.dependencies]` in `/Cargo.toml`:\n  - `axum = { version = \"0.8\", features = [\"ws\"] }` (was `\"0.7\"`)\n  - `tower = \"0.5\"` (was `\"0.4\"`)\n  - `tower-http = { version = \"0.6\", features = [\"trace\", \"cors\"] }` (was `\"0.5\"`)\n- Run `cargo fetch` to update `Cargo.lock`.\n- No source file changes in this stage.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** None.\n\n---\n\n### Stage 2 — Compile-error triage and fix in `ailoop-server`\n\n**Deliverable:** `cargo build -p ailoop-server` succeeds with Axum 0.8.\n\n**Scope (enumerate all files to touch):**\n- `ailoop-server/src/server/core.rs`:\n  - Fix `axum::serve(listener, built_router.into_make_service())` if `.into_make_service()` is no longer required or the call signature changed.\n  - Update the inline comment at the `nest()` call site (line 1166) from \"In axum 0.7, ...\" to reflect Axum 0.8 nesting behavior.\n  - Verify all `WsMessage::Text(t)` pattern arms compile; no action if type is unchanged.\n  - Verify all `axum::extract::ws::*` imports compile.\n- `ailoop-server/src/middleware/auth.rs`:\n  - Verify `use axum::{body::Body, ...}` import path is valid in Axum 0.8; update if `Body` moved.\n  - Verify `tower::{Layer, Service}` imports and blanket impls compile under Tower 0.5.\n- `ailoop-server/src/server/api.rs`:\n  - Verify all `axum::extract::State`, `axum::http::StatusCode`, `axum::response::IntoResponse` usages compile.\n  - Fix any method renames or trait bound changes introduced by Axum 0.8.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 1 must be complete (Cargo.lock updated).\n\n---\n\n### Stage 3 — Compile-error triage and fix in `ailoop-cli`\n\n**Deliverable:** `cargo build -p ailoop-cli` succeeds.\n\n**Scope:**\n- `ailoop-cli/src/main.rs` and all files under `ailoop-cli/src/`: inspect all direct `axum::` usages and fix any breaking changes.\n- `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml`: no version changes expected (inherits from workspace); verify no explicit `axum` pin overrides the workspace version.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 2 (ailoop-server must compile first, as ailoop-cli depends on it).\n\n---\n\n### Stage 4 — Test suite green\n\n**Deliverable:** `cargo test --workspace` passes for `ailoop-core`, `ailoop-server`, and `ailoop-cli`.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Run `cargo test -p ailoop-server` — fix any test compilation failures caused by API changes.\n- Run `cargo test -p ailoop-cli` — fix any test compilation failures.\n- Run `cargo test -p ailoop-core` — confirm no regressions (ailoop-core has no axum dependency; test run is a regression gate only).\n- Dev dependency in `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml`: `reqwest = \"0.11\"` (dev-only); confirm test builds compile.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stages 2 and 3 must be complete.\n\n---\n\n### Stage 5 — CHANGELOG update\n\n**Deliverable:** `CHANGELOG.md` updated with a migration note for embedders.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Add entry under `[Unreleased]` in `CHANGELOG.md` covering:\n  - Axum 0.7 → 0.8 bump.\n  - Tower 0.4 → 0.5 bump.\n  - tower-http 0.5 → 0.6 bump.\n  - Any signature changes to `router()` or `AiloopServer::start_with_shutdown()` discovered in Stages 2–3.\n  - Embedder migration note: \"Update your workspace's `axum` dependency to `0.8` before merging `ailoop_server::router()`.\"\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stages 2–4 must be complete (so that actual signature changes are known).\n\n---\n\n## 11. Breaking Changes\n\n| Change | Affected callers | Mitigation |\n|---|---|---|\n| `axum::Router` return type of `router()` is now Axum 0.8 | Any downstream crate (e.g., Newton) that embeds the returned `Router` | Downstream MUST update their own `axum` dep to `\"0.8\"`. Documented in `CHANGELOG.md`. |\n| `AiloopServer::start_with_shutdown()` internal: `.into_make_service()` may be removed | `AiloopServer` users calling `start()` or `start_with_shutdown()` | No API change for callers — internal fix only. |\n| `tower-http` 0.6 CorsLayer API (if any method renamed) | Any embedder that constructs `CorsConfig` and relies on `CorsLayer` behavior | `CorsConfig` struct fields are unchanged; internal `build_cors_layer()` function absorbs any API delta. |\n| Minimum Rust edition / compiler version may increase | CI pipelines pinning an older `rustc` | Verify Newton's `rust-toolchain.toml` is compatible. |\n\n---\n\n## 12. Modified Files and Summary\n\n| File / Path | Summary of modifications |\n|---|---|\n| `Cargo.toml` | Bump `axum` to `\"0.8\"`, `tower` to `\"0.5\"`, `tower-http` to `\"0.6\"` in `[workspace.dependencies]` |\n| `ailoop-server/src/server/core.rs` | Fix `axum::serve(...)` call (remove or adapt `.into_make_service()`); update nesting comment; fix any WS/body import paths |\n| `ailoop-server/src/middleware/auth.rs` | Update `axum::body::Body` import if path changed; verify `tower` 0.5 `Layer`/`Service` impls compile |\n| `ailoop-server/src/server/api.rs` | Fix any axum 0.8 handler/extractor API changes |\n| `ailoop-cli/src/main.rs` | Fix any direct `axum::` usages broken by 0.8 upgrade (if any) |\n| `CHANGELOG.md` | Add embedder migration note for Axum 0.8 / Tower 0.5 / tower-http 0.6 |\n\n> **Note:** `ailoop-server/Cargo.toml`, `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml`, and `ailoop-core/Cargo.toml` do not require version edits — all inherit via `{ workspace = true }`. `ailoop-core` has no `axum` dependency and requires no changes.\n\n---\n\n## 13. Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Blocking? | Gates stage | Notes if skipped |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Axum 0.8 crate (crates.io) | External library | Yes | Stage 1 | Cannot proceed without published crate |\n| Tower 0.5 crate (crates.io) | External library | Yes | Stage 1 | Cannot proceed without published crate |\n| tower-http 0.6 crate (crates.io) | External library | Yes | Stage 1 | Cannot proceed without published crate |\n| Axum 0.7 → 0.8 migration guide (upstream docs) | Reference | Non-blocking | Stage 2 | Implementer should consult https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/releases/tag/axum-v0.8.0 for full breaking-changes list |\n| Newton workspace `Cargo.toml` (read-only reference) | External reference | Non-blocking | Stage 5 | Used only to confirm exact patch versions; not required to merge |\n| CI pipeline (cargo test) | Internal | Non-blocking | Stage 4 | Tests can run locally; CI validates before merge |\n\n---\n\n## 14. Proposed Folder Structure\n\nNo new files or directories are created by this spec. Only existing files are modified (see Section 12). The workspace structure is unchanged:\n\n```\nailoop/                          ← workspace root\n├── Cargo.toml                   ← MODIFIED: version bumps\n├── Cargo.lock                   ← MODIFIED: regenerated by cargo fetch\n├── CHANGELOG.md                 ← MODIFIED: migration note\n├── ailoop-core/                 ← unchanged\n│   └── Cargo.toml\n├── ailoop-server/               ← source fixes\n│   ├── Cargo.toml               ← unchanged (inherits workspace)\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── lib.rs               ← unchanged\n│       ├── config.rs            ← unchanged\n│       ├── error.rs             ← unchanged\n│       ├── state.rs             ← unchanged\n│       ├── middleware/\n│       │   └── auth.rs          ← MODIFIED: tower 0.5 / axum body import\n│       └── server/\n│           ├── api.rs           ← MODIFIED: axum 0.8 handler fixes\n│           ├── core.rs          ← MODIFIED: axum::serve call + comment\n│           └── ...              ← other server files unchanged\n└── ailoop-cli/\n    ├── Cargo.toml               ← unchanged (inherits workspace)\n    └── src/\n        └── main.rs              ← MODIFIED if direct axum usages exist\n```\n\n---\n\n## 15. Design Decisions\n\n| # | Question | Decision | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Should `reqwest` be bumped to 0.12 in this PR? | No — defer to a follow-up | Out of scope per user spec; keeps this PR focused and avoids unrelated breakage |\n| 2 | Should exact patch versions (e.g., `axum = \"0.8.1\"`) be pinned or use semver range? | Use `\"0.8\"` (minor-compatible range) | Matches Newton's approach; allows patch updates without lockfile churn |\n| 3 | Should `ailoop-server` expose an `axum` re-export so embedders don't need their own dep? | No — embedders declare `axum = \"0.8\"` themselves | Re-exporting Axum types from a library crate causes version-mismatch problems if the embedder's semver range differs |\n| 4 | Should the `AiloopServer` convenience wrapper be removed in favor of the composable API only? | No — keep for backward compatibility | Existing standalone `ailoop serve` users depend on it; removal is a separate breaking-change decision |\n| 5 | Should `tower-http` trace feature be retained after 0.6 bump? | Yes — keep `[\"trace\", \"cors\"]` feature set | Used for request tracing; removing it would silently drop observability |\n\n---\n\n## 16. Out of Scope (Explicit)\n\n- Bumping `reqwest` from `0.11` to `0.12` in `ailoop-server/Cargo.toml` or `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml` (dev-deps).\n- Any Newton-side changes to merge `ailoop_server::router()` into `newton serve`.\n- Changes to `ailoop-core` (no axum dependency; not affected).\n- Changes to `ailoop-py` or `ailoop-js`.\n- Adding new HTTP endpoints or modifying the REST/WebSocket protocol.\n- Refactoring the `AuthMiddleware` implementation beyond what is required to compile under Tower 0.5.\n- Adding new Axum 0.8 features (e.g., `axum-extra` extractors, typed routing).\n- CI pipeline configuration changes (e.g., updating `rust-toolchain.toml`).\n- Changing the `ServeConfig` struct fields or `AiloopError` variants.\n- Aligning `tokio-tungstenite` version (not directly coupled to Axum version).\n\n---\n\n## 17. References\n\n| Entity | Location | Note |\n|---|---|---|\n| Workspace dependency declarations | `/Cargo.toml` lines 20–22 | `axum`, `tower`, `tower-http` to be updated |\n| `router()` function | `ailoop-server/src/server/core.rs:1139–1169` | Primary axum API call site; `axum::serve` at line 135 |\n| `axum::serve(...)` call | `ailoop-server/src/server/core.rs:135` | `.into_make_service()` call to verify against Axum 0.8 |\n| Auth middleware `Layer`/`Service` impls | `ailoop-server/src/middleware/auth.rs:33–88` | Tower 0.5 compatibility check point |\n| `AiloopAppState` struct | `ailoop-server/src/state.rs:15–30` | Public embed state type |\n| Public API exports | `ailoop-server/src/lib.rs:1–17` | Canonical list of exported symbols |\n| `ServeConfig` / `AuthConfig` / `CorsConfig` | `ailoop-server/src/config.rs:5–37` | Embed configuration types |\n| `AiloopError` enum | `ailoop-server/src/error.rs:3–21` | Error type to preserve |\n| `ailoop-cli` axum usage | `ailoop-cli/Cargo.toml:25` | CLI inherits axum from workspace; check `src/main.rs` for direct usages |\n| CHANGELOG existing embedder section | `CHANGELOG.md:4–30` | Existing embedder API documentation; add migration note here |\n| Newton reference workspace | `https://github.com/gonewton/newton/blob/main/Cargo.toml` | Target axum/tower/tower-http versions to match |\n| Axum 0.8 release notes | `https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/releases/tag/axum-v0.8.0` | Authoritative breaking-changes list |","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goailoop/ailoop/issues/59/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http/issues/832","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http/issues/832/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http/issues/832/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http/issues/832/events","html_url":"https://github.com/hyperium/http/issues/832","id":4370142634,"node_id":"I_kwDOBRC9Es8AAAABBHsVqg","number":832,"title":"Optional Bodies","user":{"login":"lorenzleutgeb","id":542154,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU0MjE1NA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/542154?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb","html_url":"https://github.com/lorenzleutgeb","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/lorenzleutgeb/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-02T21:51:57Z","updated_at":"2026-05-04T21:59:28Z","closed_at":"2026-05-04T21:59:28Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"As of 2026-05-02 with `master` at `68e0abb`, both `Request` and `Response` always carry a body:\nhttps://github.com/hyperium/http/blob/68e0abb052a243a5530ad4c404cb0b169a7ecb4a/src/request.rs#L154\nhttps://github.com/hyperium/http/blob/68e0abb052a243a5530ad4c404cb0b169a7ecb4a/src/response.rs#L176\n\nI would like to understand why this is the case, as opposed to both aforementioned lines reading `body: Option<T>`. My main motivation for this is that I ran into a bug downstream of `http`, which is related to the \"empty body\": https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3741\n\nI have found various other cases where the \"empty body\" seems to have caused trouble in one way or another:\n\n - https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/730\n - https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/747\n - https://github.com/hyperium/hyper/discussions/3707 (with more references; closed without resolution)\n\nI believe that many of these edge cases around the \"empty body\" would have been less problematic if bodies were `Option<T>`.\n\nWas it an intentional design decision to not have bodies be `Option<T>` but plain `T`? If so, what were the reasons?\n\nI do realize that changing this would likely mean a major version bump because consequentially, at the very least, `fn body(&self) -> &T` on both `Request` and `Response` would have to be changed to `fn body(&self) -> Option<&T>`.\n\nContrast this with various RFCs and other well-known documentation on HTTP which all mention some flavor of optionality for bodies (emphasis mine):\n\n#### HTTP/1.0\n\n[RFC 1945 (HTTP/1.0), Section 7.1 (Entity Body)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc1945#section-7.2):\n> The entity body **(if any)** sent with an HTTP request or response is […]\n\n#### HTTP/1.1\n\n[RFC 2616 (HTTP/1.1), Section 4.3 (Message Body)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc2616#section-4.3):\n> The message-body **(if any)** of an HTTP message […]\n\n#### HTTP Semantics\n\n[RFC 9110 (HTTP Semantics), Section 6.4 (Content Semantics), Paragraph 1](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9110#section-6.4-1):\n> HTTP messages **often** transfer a complete or partial representation as the message \"content\": a stream of octets sent after the header section, […]\n\n#### HTTP/2\n\n[RFC 9113 (HTTP/2), Section 8.1 (HTTP Message Framing), Paragraph 3, Item 2](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9113#section-8.1-3.2):\n> […] **zero or more** DATA frames containing the message content […]\n\nThe [examples in RFC 9113 (HTTP/2), Section 8.8 (Examples)](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9113#section-8.8) show \"Simple Request\" and \"Simple Response\", both without a body, followed by \"Complex Request\" with a body.\n\n#### HTTP/3\n\n[RFC 9114 (HTTP/3), Section 4.1 (HTTP Message Framing), Paragraph 5, Item 2](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc9114#section-4.1-5.2):\n> […] optionally, the content, **if present**, sent as a series of DATA frames, and […]\n\n#### MDN\n\nThe [MDN Guide on \"HTTP Messages\", Section \"Anatomy of an HTTP Message\"](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/HTTP/Guides/Messages#anatomy_of_an_http_message):\n> An **optional** body containing data associated with the message. […] **Whether a message contains a body or not** is determined by the start-line and HTTP headers.\n\n/cc @hxzhao527","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http/issues/832/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http/issues/832/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Takazudo/zudo-front-builder/issues/370","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Takazudo/zudo-front-builder","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Takazudo/zudo-front-builder/issues/370/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Takazudo/zudo-front-builder/issues/370/commen