ssues/365\n\n---\n\n**Wave:** 4\n**Execution mode:** subagents — single child does the lifecycle implementation; no peer coordination\n**Model:** opus — public Rust crate surface design; needs careful judgment to keep the API generic and the public-method count under 10\n\n**Depends on:** Sub-task 2.3 (#369) — gaps confirmed working before the embed API builds on them\n\n## What to do\n\nImplement the embed API **lifecycle** surface — builder, ServerMode, ServerHandle, request-extension middleware. SSR-handler integration is the separate sub-task 3.1b.\n\n1. Read `research/346-embed-as-library-api.md` on main for the API spec; cross-reference `crates/zfb/src/v8_host_adapter.rs` for the threading pattern.\n2. In `crates/zfb-server/src/lib.rs`, add public types:\n   - `Server::builder()` returning `ServerBuilder`\n   - `ServerBuilder` with methods: `config_path`, `mode(ServerMode)`, `bind`, `with_request_extension<T: Clone + Send + Sync + 'static>`, `build`\n   - `ServerMode::{Dev, Preview, Embed}` enum\n   - Terminal methods on `Server`: `serve`, `serve_in_thread`\n   - `ServerHandle` with `addr()`, `shutdown()` (**idempotent**), `join()`\n3. **`with_request_extension` shape (per Pinned design choice):** implement as a **tower middleware layer** in `crates/zfb-server/src/middleware.rs` (new file or similar). The layer calls `req.extensions_mut().insert(value.clone())` per request. **Do NOT publicly re-export `axum::Extension<T>`.** Document the consumer-side retrieval: `req.extensions().get::<T>()` inside their handler.\n4. **`serve_in_thread` pattern (per Pinned design choice):** mirror `crates/zfb/src/v8_host_adapter.rs`. Dedicated OS thread + current-thread tokio runtime + channel-based shutdown messaging.\n5. **`shutdown()` idempotency:** second call is a no-op. Cover with a test.\n6. Verify public-method count on Server + ServerBuilder is ≤ 10. `ServerHandle`'s methods don't count toward this budget.\n7. Add a smoke test in `crates/zfb-server/tests/embed_lifecycle_smoke.rs`: build server with builder → bind ephemeral port → embed in foreign tokio runtime → shutdown via handle's oneshot → `shutdown()` called twice is OK.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- `cargo build -p zfb-server` clean\n- `cargo test -p zfb-server` passes the lifecycle smoke test (build + bind + serve + shutdown + double-shutdown)\n- Public-method count on `Server` + `ServerBuilder` ≤ 10\n- `with_request_extension` does NOT publicly export `axum::Extension`\n- No regressions in existing `zfb-server` tests\n\n## What this sub-task does NOT include\n\n- `with_ssr_handler` (that's Sub-task 3.1b)\n- Example crate (also 3.1b — moved from `__inbox/346-zfb-embed-spike/` then)\n- Docs page (3.1b adds the SSR-aware how-to)\n\n## Generic-vs-specific check\n\n✓ Generic. Any Rust host wanting to embed zfb (Tauri, a Rust web app, a CLI tool) benefits.\n\n**Base branch:** `base/trial-followup-roadmap` — PR targets this branch (which itself targets `main`).\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Takazudo/zudo-front-builder/issues/370/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Takazudo/zudo-front-builder/issues/370/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-opensovd/classic-diagnostic-adapter/issues/204","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-opensovd/classic-diagnostic-adapter","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-opensovd/classic-diagnostic-adapter/issues/204/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-opensovd/classic-diagnostic-adapter/issues/204/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/eclipse-opensovd/classic-diagnostic-adapter/issues/204/events","html_url":"https://github.com/eclipse-opensovd/classic-diagnostic-adapter/issues/204","id":3961554751,"node_id":"I_kwDOPSDe4M7sIIc_","n