tate_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body/issues/168","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body/issues/168/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body/issues/168/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body/issues/168/events","html_url":"https://github.com/hyperium/http-body/issues/168","id":4416795048,"node_id":"I_kwDOCuynzM8AAAABB0LxqA","number":168,"title":"`BodyExt::collect` isn't fair","user":{"login":"punkeel","id":1859135,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE4NTkxMzU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1859135?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel","html_url":"https://github.com/punkeel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/punkeel/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":9,"created_at":"2026-05-10T20:51:02Z","updated_at":"2026-05-11T18:00:50Z","closed_at":"2026-05-11T16:13:15Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Hi. I think [`http_body_util::BodyExt::collect`](https://docs.rs/http-body-util/latest/http_body_util/trait.BodyExt.html#method.collect) has a cooperative scheduling fairness issue that can show up through higher-level clients like reqwest ([`reqwest::Response::bytes()`](https://docs.rs/reqwest/latest/reqwest/struct.Response.html#method.bytes)).\n\nThe short version: `Collect` appears to poll the inner body in a loop, appending every immediately-ready frame until the body returns `Pending` or EOF. Because that loop happens inside one `Future::poll()` call, it is not an .await boundary from the executor's perspective. If the body keeps returning `Poll::Ready(Some(frame))`, Tokio does not get a chance to schedule other tasks until collection finishes.\n\nThis looks very similar to the starvation case described in [Tokio's cooperative preemption post](https://tokio.rs/blog/2020-04-preemption).\n\nTokio's budget helps when Tokio resources participate in cooperative scheduling, but `Collect` is runtime-agnostic and, as far as I can tell, does not itself consume a cooperative budget or voluntarily return Pending after draining some amount of ready work.\n\n**Impact**\n\nThis means a call path like:\n\n```rust\nlet bytes = reqwest::get(url).await?.bytes().await?;\n```\n\ncan create a long single task poll when the response body is large, already buffered, or decoded in-process. From the application's point of view this is surprising: the code contains an .await, but the awaited future's semantic unit is _collect the whole body_, so it may do a large amount of synchronous work before yielding.\n\nIn production, this can block a Tokio worker long enough to delay unrelated tasks. We observed slow task polls above 20ms in a latency-sensitive service. Switching from full-body collection to chunked reads with explicit fairness points avoided the issue:\n\n```rust\nwhile let Some(chunk) = response.chunk().await? {\n    // process or buffer chunk\n}\n```\n\n**Seemingly Root Cause**\n\nThe root cause seems to be this [code](https://github.com/hyperium/http-body/blob/c8cb37f9ce2f8723b25e1ef1a9f6cb63ef1f9c54/http-body-util/src/combinators/collect.rs#L29-L43)):\n\n```\nreqwest::Response::bytes()\n  -> http_body_util::BodyExt::collect()\n  -> http_body_util::combinators::Collect\n  -> poll inner Body in a loop\n```\n\nThe loop is not an .await; it is one `poll()` implementation repeatedly calling `poll_frame()`. If every `poll_frame()` returns Ready, the collector can keep running synchronously.\n\n\n**Possible fixes**\n\n\nIs this expected behavior for Collect?\n\nIf so, it may be worth documenting prominently that collect() is not executor-fair for large or always-ready bodies, and callers that care about event-loop latency should consume frames/chunks manually.\n\nIf not, maybe `Collect` should include some kind of budget, such as returning `Pending` after some number of frames or bytes and waking itself, or exposing a configurable fair collection helper. I realize http-body-util is runtime-agnostic, so depending directly on Tokio coop APIs may not be appropriate, but some generic frame/byte budget could still avoid pathological single-poll drains.\n\n\n\nkudos to @Noah-Kennedy for https://github.com/tokio-rs/tokio/pull/8136","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body/issues/168/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/hyperium/http-body/issues/168/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton/issues/351","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton/issues/351/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton/issues/351/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton/issues/351/events","html_url":"https://github.com/gonewton/newton/issues/351","id":4444048300,"node_id":"I_kwDOQ9y5xc8AAAABCOLLrA","number":351,"title":"Embed ailoop-server in newton serve (opt-in, single listener)","user":{"login":"aroff","id":4482374,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0ODIzNzQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4482374?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff","html_url":"https://github.com/aroff","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-14T07:23:53Z","updated_at":"2026-05-14T13:19:29Z","closed_at":"2026-05-14T13:19:29Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"---\nissue: 351\nbranch: feature/351-embed-ailoop-server-in-newton-serve-opt-in-single-listener\nboard_item_id: PVTI_lADODzvwg84BRFnrzgstFAs\nsource: github-project\n---\n\n# 351 — Embed ailoop-server in `newton serve` (opt-in, single listener)\n\n**Repository scope:** `gonewton/newton` only. Upstream Axum alignment is tracked in `goailoop/ailoop#59`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem statement\n\nToday, running `newton serve` and using the ailoop human-in-the-loop operator together requires two separate long-running processes: `newton serve` (port 8080 by default) and `ailoop serve` (a separate port). This two-process model complicates deployment—operators must configure, start, monitor, and expose two ports. Newton has already solved an analogous problem for MCP: `newton serve --with-mcp` merges the MCP HTTP router onto the same Axum listener using `app.merge(mcp_router)` after validating the mount path. There is no equivalent mechanism for ailoop-server. `ailoop-server` currently targets an older Axum version and cannot be merged into Newton's Axum 0.8 router; that upstream prerequisite is tracked in `goailoop/ailoop#59`.\n\n**Out of scope:** Changes to `newton run`, `newton batch`, or any other command; changes to ailoop-core's WebSocket client integration; changes to the upstream `ailoop-server` crate itself (tracked separately); multi-prefix or multi-ailoop-instance embedding.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Goals\n\n1. Introduce `newton serve --with-embedded-ailoop` (and `--ailoop-base-path <PATH>`, default `/ailoop`) as opt-in flags that merge an `ailoop_server::router()` into the same Axum listener as the Newton REST API.\n2. Validate `--ailoop-base-path` for shape and route collision before any server resources are allocated, following the same validation contract already in place for `--mcp-path`.\n3. Add `CancellationToken`-based graceful shutdown to `newton serve` so that ailoop background tasks (spawned via `spawn_background_tasks`) are cancelled when the process receives a shutdown signal or `axum::serve` exits.\n4. Emit a single structured JSON event (`ailoop_serve_started`) on stderr when embedded mode starts, parallel to the existing `mcp_serve_started` event.\n5. Update operator documentation (config precedence note) so operators know `ailoop_server_ws_url` / `NEWTON_AILOOP_WS_URL` must include the WebSocket path under the chosen `base_path`.\n6. Provide an integration test that starts `newton serve --with-embedded-ailoop` on an ephemeral port and asserts that the ailoop health endpoint responds with HTTP 200 under the configured base path.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Current behavior\n\n| Component | Role | Mutable at runtime? |\n|---|---|---|\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/args.rs : ServeArgs` | CLI argument struct for `newton serve`; holds `host`, `port`, `static_ui`, `with_mcp`, `mcp_path` | No — parsed once at startup |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs : serve()` | Async fn: validates paths, builds `AppState`, merges optional MCP router, binds `TcpListener`, calls `axum::serve` | No |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs : validate_mcp_path()` | Checks path shape (leading slash, not `/`, no trailing slash) | No |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs : ensure_no_route_collision()` | Checks `--mcp-path` against `NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES` | No |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs : NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES` | Constant slice: `/health`, `/workflows`, `/hil`, `/streaming`, `/operators`, `/dashboard`, `/portfolio`, `/opportunities`, `/requests`, `/plans`, `/persistence`, `/testing` | No |\n| `crates/core/src/integrations/ailoop/config.rs : AiloopConfig` | Struct holding `ws_url`, `channel`, `enabled`, `fail_fast`; loaded from env vars or `.newton/configs/monitor.conf` | No |\n| `crates/core/src/api/mod.rs : create_router()` | Builds the Newton REST `axum::Router` with CORS | No |\n\n**Current build flow:** `cargo build` for the `newton` binary in `crates/cli`; no `ailoop-server` crate is referenced anywhere in the workspace.\n\n**Current serve flow:** `serve()` optionally merges the MCP router, binds a `TcpListener`, then calls `axum::serve(listener, app.into_make_service()).await` with no graceful shutdown. There is no `CancellationToken` in the serve path today.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Design\n\n### 4.1 Flag design\n\n`ServeArgs` gains two new optional fields following the exact same clap 4.x pattern as `with_mcp` / `mcp_path`:\n\n```\n--with-embedded-ailoop        (bool, default false)\n--ailoop-base-path <PATH>     (String, default \"/ailoop\"; only meaningful when --with-embedded-ailoop is set)\n```\n\nWhen `--with-embedded-ailoop` is absent (the default), the serve function MUST behave identically to today. No behaviour change for existing callers.\n\n### 4.2 Path validation rules\n\n`validate_ailoop_path(p: &str)` MUST reject paths that:\n- Are empty\n- Do not start with `/`\n- Equal the bare root `/`\n- End with `/` when length > 1\n- Equal `/api` exactly (ailoop internal routes are rooted at `/api` under the base path; mounting at `/api` would collide internally)\n\n`ensure_no_ailoop_path_collision(ailoop_path: &str, mcp_path_if_active: Option<&str>)` MUST reject:\n- Any value equal to, a strict ancestor of, or a strict descendant of any entry in `NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES` (same logic as `ensure_no_route_collision`)\n- Any value equal to `mcp_path_if_active` when `--with-mcp` is also enabled (mutual collision)\n\nBoth validation functions MUST be called before any server resources (store, socket) are allocated—at the same point as MCP path validation today (`commands.rs:1776–1779`).\n\n### 4.3 Router merge\n\nWhen `--with-embedded-ailoop` is set:\n\n1. Construct `Arc<AiloopAppState>` from the ailoop-server API.\n2. Construct `ServeConfig { base_path: args.ailoop_base_path.clone() }`. Per the **minimal-serve-config** API contract (§5.4), `ServeConfig` exposes only `base_path: String`. Ailoop's auth and web settings are env/config-driven inside ailoop-server and are not passed from Newton at construction time.\n3. Call `ailoop_server::router(state, config)` to obtain an `axum::Router`.\n4. Merge: `app = app.merge(ailoop_router)`.\n5. Call `spawn_background_tasks(&state, &cancel_token)` before `axum::serve`.\n\n### 4.4 Graceful shutdown\n\nToday `axum::serve` is called without graceful shutdown:\n```rust\naxum::serve(listener, app.into_make_service()).await\n```\n\nThis MUST be replaced with `with_graceful_shutdown` when embedded ailoop is active (to cancel background tasks). The recommended approach is to add a `CancellationToken` unconditionally to `serve()` so the pattern is consistent:\n\n```rust\nlet cancel = CancellationToken::new();\n// ... optional: spawn_background_tasks(&ailoop_state, &cancel.clone()) ...\naxum::serve(listener, app.into_make_service())\n    .with_graceful_shutdown(cancel.clone().cancelled_owned())\n    .await\n```\n\nOn `axum::serve` return (normal or error), call `cancel.cancel()` so background tasks exit.\n\n### 4.5 Structured startup event\n\nWhen `--with-embedded-ailoop` is active, after the bind succeeds and before `axum::serve`, emit to stderr:\n\n```json\n{\"event\":\"ailoop_serve_started\",\"ailoop_enabled\":true,\"bind_address\":\"<host>:<port>\",\"ailoop_base_path\":\"<path>\"}\n```\n\nThis MUST mirror the `mcp_serve_started` pattern at `commands.rs:1886–1890`. Both events MAY be emitted in the same run if both `--with-mcp` and `--with-embedded-ailoop` are active.\n\n### 4.6 ailoop_server_ws_url path note\n\nWhen `--with-embedded-ailoop` is active, the WebSocket URL that ailoop clients (e.g. the HIL operator) must use follows `ailoop-server`'s path rules under `ServeConfig.base_path`. For default base path `/ailoop`, the WS URL is typically `ws://127.0.0.1:8080/ailoop/<ws-path>`. Operators MUST update `ailoop_server_ws_url` in `.newton/configs/monitor.conf` (or `NEWTON_AILOOP_WS_URL`) to include this path prefix.\n\n### 4.7 CORS behaviour\n\nNewton applies permissive CORS via `tower-http` on its router at `crates/core/src/api/mod.rs`. After `app.merge(ailoop_router)`, the merged router inherits Newton's CORS layer. Implementers MUST verify that browser or UI clients targeting ailoop WebSocket/REST routes through the merged router receive correct CORS headers. If ailoop-server's router applies its own CORS layer, the two layers may conflict; the outer Newton layer takes precedence in Axum's middleware ordering. Testing MUST confirm `OPTIONS` preflight on an ailoop route returns a 2xx.\n\n### 4.8 Binary size\n\n`ailoop-server` MUST be added with `default-features = false`. Features beyond the core HTTP router (e.g. Telegram integration, if present as a feature flag) MUST NOT be enabled unless explicitly required for embedded mode.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Schema and API\n\n### 5.1 `ServeArgs` — modified struct\n\n**File:** `crates/cli/src/cli/args.rs`\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Args, Clone, Debug)]\npub struct ServeArgs {\n    /// Host address to bind the server to (default: 127.0.0.1)\n    #[arg(long, default_value = \"127.0.0.1\")]\n    pub host: String,\n\n    /// Port to listen on (default: 8080)\n    #[arg(long, default_value = \"8080\")]\n    pub port: u16,\n\n    /// Path to the built Newton UI dist directory (optional)\n    #[arg(long = \"static-ui\", value_name = \"PATH\")]\n    pub static_ui: Option<PathBuf>,\n\n    /// Mount the MCP HTTP router on the same listener as the Newton API.\n    #[arg(long = \"with-mcp\", default_value_t = false)]\n    pub with_mcp: bool,\n\n    /// Path prefix at which the MCP HTTP router is mounted (used only with --with-mcp).\n    #[arg(long = \"mcp-path\", default_value = \"/mcp\")]\n    pub mcp_path: String,\n\n    /// Embed the ailoop HTTP/WebSocket server on the same listener as the Newton API.\n    #[arg(long = \"with-embedded-ailoop\", default_value_t = false)]\n    pub with_embedded_ailoop: bool,\n\n    /// Path prefix at which the embedded ailoop router is mounted\n    /// (used only with --with-embedded-ailoop). Must not be `/api`.\n    #[arg(long = \"ailoop-base-path\", default_value = \"/ailoop\")]\n    pub ailoop_base_path: String,\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 Validation functions — new\n\n**File:** `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs`\n\n```rust\n/// Validate `--ailoop-base-path` shape.\n/// Returns NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001 for: empty, no leading slash, bare `/`,\n/// trailing slash, or exactly `/api`.\nfn validate_ailoop_path(p: &str) -> StdResult<(), AppError>;\n\n/// Reject `--ailoop-base-path` values that collide with Newton REST route\n/// prefixes (NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-002) or with --mcp-path when --with-mcp is\n/// also active (NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-003).\nfn ensure_no_ailoop_path_collision(\n    ailoop_path: &str,\n    mcp_path_if_active: Option<&str>,\n) -> StdResult<(), AppError>;\n```\n\n### 5.3 Error codes — constants\n\n**File:** `crates/cli/src/cli/framework_setup.rs` (in `pub mod error_codes`)\n\n```rust\n/// serve --with-embedded-ailoop: invalid --ailoop-base-path shape.\npub const NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_001: &str = \"NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001\";\n/// serve --with-embedded-ailoop: --ailoop-base-path collides with Newton REST prefix.\npub const NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_002: &str = \"NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-002\";\n/// serve --with-embedded-ailoop: --ailoop-base-path collides with --mcp-path.\npub const NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_003: &str = \"NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-003\";\n/// serve --with-embedded-ailoop: ailoop_server::router() returned an error.\npub const NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_004: &str = \"NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004\";\n```\n\n### 5.4 ailoop-server types — required API contract\n\nThe following types are consumed from `ailoop-server` once the Axum 0.8 upgrade (goailoop/ailoop#59) is merged.\n\n**Design decision:** The **minimal-serve-config** alternative is adopted (the user-selected alternative id `\"null\"` was not found in clarify.json; the recommendation was applied instead). Newton imports only `ServeConfig { base_path }` and a no-arg `AiloopAppState::new()`. Web, auth, and CORS settings are env/config-driven inside ailoop-server; Newton does not pass them. This contract must be confirmed with the upstream ailoop team before Stage 2 proceeds — specifically: (a) that `AiloopAppState::new()` takes no arguments, and (b) that `router()` returns `Result<axum::Router, E>` rather than a bare `axum::Router`.\n\n```rust\n// From ailoop-server (upstream — required minimal surface)\npub struct AiloopAppState { /* opaque */ }\nimpl AiloopAppState {\n    /// No-arg constructor; reads ailoop configuration (channel, database path,\n    /// etc.) from environment variables or ailoop's own config files.\n    /// Newton does not pass config values in.\n    pub fn new() -> Arc<Self>;\n}\n\npub struct ServeConfig {\n    /// The URL path prefix under which all ailoop routes are mounted.\n    /// Newton sets this from --ailoop-base-path. No other fields are required\n    /// at embed time; all other ailoop settings are env/config-driven.\n    pub base_path: String,\n}\n\n/// Returns an axum::Router with all ailoop HTTP/WebSocket routes mounted under\n/// config.base_path. Returns Err if base_path is invalid or router construction\n/// fails (Newton maps this error to NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004).\npub fn router(state: Arc<AiloopAppState>, config: ServeConfig) -> Result<axum::Router, impl std::error::Error>;\n\n/// Spawns ailoop background tasks bound to the given cancellation token.\n/// Must be called before axum::serve. Tasks exit when cancel_token is cancelled.\npub fn spawn_background_tasks(\n    state: &Arc<AiloopAppState>,\n    cancel_token: &tokio_util::sync::CancellationToken,\n);\n```\n\n**Open question (pre-Stage-2 gate):** If the upstream team cannot deliver a no-arg `AiloopAppState::new()` (e.g. because a database path or runtime config is required), the caller in §5.5 must be updated to pass those arguments. A spec revision will be required before Stage 2 merges.\n\n### 5.5 `serve()` — modified control flow (pseudocode)\n\n**File:** `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs`\n\n```rust\npub async fn serve(args: ServeArgs) -> StdResult<(), AppError> {\n    // 1. Validate paths (before allocating any resources)\n    if args.with_mcp {\n        validate_mcp_path(&args.mcp_path)?;\n        ensure_no_route_collision(&args.mcp_path)?;\n    }\n    if args.with_embedded_ailoop {\n        validate_ailoop_path(&args.ailoop_base_path)?;\n        ensure_no_ailoop_path_collision(\n            &args.ailoop_base_path,\n            args.with_mcp.then_some(&args.mcp_path),\n        )?;\n    }\n\n    // 2. Existing: build registry, workspace, store, AppState, Newton router\n    // ... (unchanged) ...\n\n    // 3. Optional: merge MCP router (unchanged)\n    if args.with_mcp { /* ... existing ... */ }\n\n    // 4. Optional: build and merge ailoop router\n    let ailoop_state: Option<Arc<AiloopAppState>> = if args.with_embedded_ailoop {\n        let config = ServeConfig { base_path: args.ailoop_base_path.clone(), /* ... */ };\n        let state = Arc::new(AiloopAppState::new(/* ... */));\n        let ailoop_router = ailoop_server::router(Arc::clone(&state), config)\n            .map_err(|e| AppError::new(ErrorCategory::IoError,\n                format!(\"NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004: {e}\")).with_code(\"NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004\"))?;\n        app = app.merge(ailoop_router);\n        Some(state)\n    } else {\n        None\n    };\n\n    // 5. Bind\n    let listener = TcpListener::bind(&socket_addr).await?;\n\n    // 6. Graceful shutdown token + background tasks\n    let cancel = CancellationToken::new();\n    if let Some(ref state) = ailoop_state {\n        ailoop_server::spawn_background_tasks(state, &cancel.clone());\n    }\n\n    // 7. Structured startup events\n    if args.with_embedded_ailoop {\n        eprintln!(\"{}\", serde_json::json!({\n            \"event\": \"ailoop_serve_started\",\n            \"ailoop_enabled\": true,\n            \"bind_address\": format!(\"{}:{}\", args.host, args.port),\n            \"ailoop_base_path\": args.ailoop_base_path,\n        }));\n    }\n\n    // 8. Serve with graceful shutdown\n    axum::serve(listener, app.into_make_service())\n        .with_graceful_shutdown(cancel.clone().cancelled_owned())\n        .await\n        .map_err(|e| AppError::new(ErrorCategory::IoError, format!(\"server error: {e}\")))?;\n\n    cancel.cancel(); // ensure background tasks exit on normal serve exit\n    Ok(())\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Error codes\n\n| Code | Category | Trigger |\n|---|---|---|\n| `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` | `ValidationError` | `--ailoop-base-path` is empty, lacks a leading `/`, equals `/`, ends with `/`, or equals `/api` |\n| `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-002` | `ValidationError` | `--ailoop-base-path` equals, is a strict ancestor of, or is a strict descendant of any entry in `NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES` |\n| `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-003` | `ValidationError` | `--ailoop-base-path` equals `--mcp-path` when both `--with-embedded-ailoop` and `--with-mcp` are active |\n| `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004` | `IoError` | `ailoop_server::router()` returned an error during router construction |\n\n---\n\n## 7. Acceptance criteria\n\n1. `newton serve --with-embedded-ailoop` on an ephemeral port starts successfully and the process remains alive.\n2. After startup, `GET <base_path>/api/v1/health` (ailoop health endpoint) returns HTTP 200 with a stable body.\n3. After startup with `--with-embedded-ailoop`, `GET /health` (Newton REST health) returns HTTP 200 on the same port.\n4. A single `{\"event\":\"ailoop_serve_started\",\"ailoop_enabled\":true,...}` JSON line appears on stderr before the server starts accepting requests.\n5. The `ailoop_serve_started` event MUST contain `bind_address` matching `<host>:<port>` and `ailoop_base_path` matching the configured path.\n6. `newton serve` without `--with-embedded-ailoop` passes all existing tests without modification; no behaviour change is observable.\n7. `--ailoop-base-path \"\"` (empty string) exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` in stderr.\n8. `--ailoop-base-path ailoop` (no leading slash) exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` in stderr.\n9. `--ailoop-base-path /` exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` in stderr.\n10. `--ailoop-base-path /ailoop/` (trailing slash) exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` in stderr.\n11. `--ailoop-base-path /api` exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` in stderr.\n12. `--ailoop-base-path /health` exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-002` in stderr (collision with Newton REST prefix).\n13. `--ailoop-base-path /workflows` exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-002` in stderr.\n14. `--with-mcp --with-embedded-ailoop --mcp-path /mcp --ailoop-base-path /mcp` exits non-zero with `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-003` in stderr.\n15. `--with-mcp --with-embedded-ailoop --mcp-path /mcp --ailoop-base-path /ailoop` starts successfully (no collision).\n16. When both `--with-mcp` and `--with-embedded-ailoop` are active, both `mcp_serve_started` and `ailoop_serve_started` JSON lines appear on stderr.\n17. `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001` through `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004` appear as constants in `error_codes` module (`framework_setup.rs`).\n18. `test_command_metadata.rs` passes with the new flags present (no metadata regression).\n19. `ailoop-server` is added with `default-features = false` in `Cargo.toml`; `cargo build` succeeds.\n20. A `CancellationToken` is used for graceful shutdown; `spawn_background_tasks` is called and cancelled on process exit.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Functionality comparison (before vs after)\n\n| Area | Before | After (flag enabled) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Processes needed for HIL | Two (`newton serve` + `ailoop serve`) | One (`newton serve --with-embedded-ailoop`) |\n| TCP listeners | Two ports required if both run | One port; Newton API + ailoop routes merged |\n| `--with-embedded-ailoop` flag | Does not exist | Opt-in flag on `newton serve` |\n| `--ailoop-base-path` flag | Does not exist | Configures ailoop mount path (default `/ailoop`) |\n| Graceful shutdown | Not present; `axum::serve` awaits without cancellation | `CancellationToken`-based; background tasks cancelled on exit |\n| `ailoop_serve_started` log event | Not emitted | Emitted on stderr as a single JSON line |\n| Path collision validation | Exists for `--mcp-path` only | Exists for both `--mcp-path` and `--ailoop-base-path`; cross-flag collision also checked |\n| `ailoop-server` dependency | Not present in workspace | Added with `default-features = false`, pinned to same git rev as `ailoop-core` after Axum 0.8 upgrade |\n| `tokio-util` dependency | Not present in `crates/cli` | Added for `CancellationToken` |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Benefit of implementing this functionality\n\nOperators running Newton for human-in-the-loop workflows today must manage two separate long-running processes, configure two ports, and expose both to clients. This creates operational overhead, increases deployment surface, and makes it harder to use Newton in constrained environments (e.g. containers with a single exposed port). Embedding ailoop-server brings Newton closer to a single-binary deployment model—the same pattern already proven by `--with-mcp`—and removes a class of configuration errors where the ailoop WS URL points at the wrong address. It also adds graceful shutdown to `newton serve` as a side effect, which benefits all serve users.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Stages\n\n### Stage 1 — Upstream unblock (external, blocking all Newton work)\n\n**Deliverable:** `goailoop/ailoop#59` merged and published: `ailoop-server` exposes `ailoop_server::router()` returning an `axum::Router` (Axum 0.8), `AiloopAppState`, `ServeConfig`, and `spawn_background_tasks`. Newton's `ailoop-core` rev in `Cargo.toml` must be bumped to include this change.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Track `goailoop/ailoop#59` to completion.\n- Confirm the public API surface: `router()`, `AiloopAppState::new()`, `ServeConfig` fields, `spawn_background_tasks()` signature, and the health endpoint path under `base_path`.\n\n**Dependency:** All Newton-side stages depend on Stage 1. Newton-side work (§5.4) MAY be designed and reviewed before Stage 1 completes but MUST NOT be merged to main until the upstream API is stable.\n\n---\n\n### Stage 2 — Cargo.toml dependency wiring\n\n**Deliverable:** `cargo build` succeeds with `ailoop-server` and `tokio-util` in the dependency graph.\n\n**Scope:**\n- `Cargo.toml` (workspace): add `ailoop-server = { git = \"https://github.com/goailoop/ailoop.git\", rev = \"<BUMPED_REV>\", default-features = false }`.\n- `Cargo.toml` (workspace): add `tokio-util = { version = \"0.7\", features = [\"sync\"] }` for `CancellationToken`.\n- `crates/cli/Cargo.toml`: add `ailoop-server = { workspace = true }` and `tokio-util = { workspace = true }`.\n- Verify `cargo check` and `cargo clippy` pass with the new crates.\n- No logic changes in this stage.\n\n**Blocks:** Stage 3, 4, 5.\n\n---\n\n### Stage 3 — CLI args and validation\n\n**Deliverable:** New flags `--with-embedded-ailoop` / `--ailoop-base-path` exist in `ServeArgs`; all validation functions and unit tests pass.\n\n**Scope:**\n- `crates/cli/src/cli/args.rs`: add `with_embedded_ailoop: bool` and `ailoop_base_path: String` to `ServeArgs` with clap 4.x `#[arg(...)]` annotations (see §5.1).\n- `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs`: implement `validate_ailoop_path(p: &str)` and `ensure_no_ailoop_path_collision(ailoop_path: &str, mcp_path_if_active: Option<&str>)` (see §5.2). Wire them into `serve()` before resource allocation (mirroring `commands.rs:1776–1779`).\n- `crates/cli/src/cli/framework_setup.rs`: add `NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_001` through `NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_004` constants to `pub mod error_codes` (see §5.3).\n- `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs`: add unit tests in `#[cfg(test)] mod serve_ailoop_validation_tests` covering: empty path, missing slash, bare `/`, trailing slash, `/api`, each entry in `NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES` as a collision, and the cross-flag `--mcp-path` collision (criteria 7–15).\n- `crates/cli/tests/integration/test_command_metadata.rs`: update if it enforces command flag parity (criterion 18).\n\n**Blocks:** Stage 4.\n\n---\n\n### Stage 4 — Serve wiring and graceful shutdown\n\n**Deliverable:** `newton serve --with-embedded-ailoop` starts, merges the ailoop router, spawns background tasks, emits the structured log event, and shuts down cleanly.\n\n**Scope:**\n- `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs : serve()`:\n  - Add `CancellationToken` (unconditional; replaces bare `axum::serve` call).\n  - When `args.with_embedded_ailoop`: construct `Arc<AiloopAppState>`, construct `ServeConfig`, call `ailoop_server::router()` (mapping error to `NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-004`), `app = app.merge(ailoop_router)`, call `spawn_background_tasks`.\n  - Emit `ailoop_serve_started` JSON line on stderr after bind, before serve.\n  - Replace `axum::serve(listener, app.into_make_service()).await` with the `with_graceful_shutdown` form.\n  - Call `cancel.cancel()` after `axum::serve` returns (normal or error path).\n- Verify: existing `axum::serve` error mapping path is preserved.\n- Verify: when `--with-embedded-ailoop` is absent, the serve function behaves identically to today (no `CancellationToken` observable side-effect; graceful shutdown is transparent).\n\n**Blocks:** Stage 5.\n\n---\n\n### Stage 5 — Integration tests\n\n**Deliverable:** Three new integration test files pass in CI; `test_command_metadata.rs` remains green.\n\n**Scope:**\n- `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_with_embedded_ailoop_health.rs`: start `newton serve --with-embedded-ailoop` on an ephemeral port (pattern from `serve_with_mcp_responds.rs`); wait for `ailoop_serve_started` JSON on stderr; assert `GET /health` (Newton REST) returns 200; assert `GET <base_path>/api/v1/health` (ailoop health) returns 200 (criterion 1, 2, 3, 4, 5).\n- `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_embedded_ailoop_path_validation.rs`: drive all NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-001 and NEWTON-SERVE-AIL-002/003 rejection cases via `assert_cmd` (criteria 7–15).\n- `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_with_mcp_and_ailoop.rs`: start `newton serve --with-mcp --with-embedded-ailoop` on an ephemeral port; assert both `mcp_serve_started` and `ailoop_serve_started` events appear on stderr; assert `/health`, `<mcp-path>`, and `<ailoop-base-path>/api/v1/health` all respond non-404 (criteria 15, 16).\n- `crates/cli/Cargo.toml`: add `[[test]]` entries for the three new test files.\n- Optional: WebSocket smoke test in `serve_with_embedded_ailoop_health.rs` if the test harness can do it without flakiness.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Breaking changes\n\n| Area | Change | Impact |\n|---|---|---|\n| `newton serve` | `axum::serve` call now uses `with_graceful_shutdown`; `CancellationToken` added to serve function | Transparent to callers; existing serve behaviour unchanged |\n| `ServeArgs` | Two new fields (`with_embedded_ailoop`, `ailoop_base_path`) | Callers that construct `ServeArgs` directly (e.g. internal unit tests) MUST add the new fields (default values apply) |\n| `framework_setup.rs error_codes` | Four new constants added | Additive; no breakage |\n| `crates/cli/Cargo.toml` | New `ailoop-server` and `tokio-util` dependencies | Binary size increase; CI build time increase (new crate to compile) |\n\nThere are no changes to the Newton REST API surface, workflow schema, checkpoint format, or any command other than `serve`.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Modified files and summary\n\n| File/path | Summary of modifications |\n|---|---|\n| `Cargo.toml` | Add `ailoop-server` workspace dependency (git, same URL as `ailoop-core`, bumped rev, `default-features = false`); add `tokio-util` workspace dependency (`features = [\"sync\"]`) |\n| `crates/cli/Cargo.toml` | Add `ailoop-server = { workspace = true }` and `tokio-util = { workspace = true }` to `[dependencies]`; add `[[test]]` entries for three new integration test files |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/args.rs` | Extend `ServeArgs` with `with_embedded_ailoop: bool` and `ailoop_base_path: String` (lines 373–394 area) |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs` | Add `validate_ailoop_path()`, `ensure_no_ailoop_path_collision()`; wire into `serve()`; add ailoop router merge block; add `CancellationToken` and `with_graceful_shutdown`; emit `ailoop_serve_started` event; add unit test module `serve_ailoop_validation_tests` (analogous to existing `serve_mcp_validation_tests` at lines 1723–1766) |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/framework_setup.rs` | Add `NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_001`–`NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_004` constants to `pub mod error_codes` (lines 70–82 area) |\n| `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_with_embedded_ailoop_health.rs` | New: integration test for embedded ailoop health endpoint |\n| `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_embedded_ailoop_path_validation.rs` | New: integration test for all path validation rejection cases |\n| `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_with_mcp_and_ailoop.rs` | New: integration test for simultaneous `--with-mcp` + `--with-embedded-ailoop` |\n| `crates/cli/tests/integration/test_command_metadata.rs` | Update if parity checks cover `ServeArgs` fields |\n\nAll paths above exist in the current workspace except the three new `tests/integration/` files.\n\n---\n\n## 13. Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Type | Blocking? | Gates stage | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `goailoop/ailoop#59` — ailoop-server Axum 0.8 upgrade | External (upstream team) | **Blocking** | Stages 2–5 | Newton cannot compile against `ailoop-server` until this is merged. Newton-side design can proceed before it lands, but the dependency addition (Stage 2) and all implementation must wait. |\n| `ailoop-server` crate (upstream) | Library | **Blocking** | Stages 2–5 | The exact public API (`AiloopAppState`, `ServeConfig`, `router()`, `spawn_background_tasks()`) is not yet finalized; see §5.4. |\n| `tokio-util = \"0.7\"` | Library (crates.io) | **Blocking** | Stage 2 | Already compatible with tokio 1.49 in this workspace; no version conflict expected. |\n| `axum = \"0.8\"` (workspace) | Library | Already present | None | Newton already uses Axum 0.8; no upgrade needed. |\n| `tower-http` CORS layer interaction with ailoop routes | Internal verification | Non-blocking | Stage 4 | MUST be verified during Stage 4 testing; no separate team dependency. |\n\n---\n\n## 14. Proposed folder structure\n\nOnly modified and new files (existing structure unchanged):\n\n```\nCargo.toml                                          ← add ailoop-server, tokio-util workspace deps\ncrates/\n  cli/\n    Cargo.toml                                      ← add ailoop-server, tokio-util; new [[test]] entries\n    src/\n      cli/\n        args.rs                                     ← extend ServeArgs\n        commands.rs                                 ← new validation fns, serve() wiring, unit tests\n        framework_setup.rs                          ← new error_codes constants\n    tests/\n      integration/\n        serve_with_embedded_ailoop_health.rs        ← NEW\n        serve_embedded_ailoop_path_validation.rs    ← NEW\n        serve_with_mcp_and_ailoop.rs                ← NEW\n        test_command_metadata.rs                    ← update if needed\n```\n\n---\n\n## 15. Design decisions\n\n| # | Question | Decision | Rationale |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Should graceful shutdown be added only when `--with-embedded-ailoop` is active, or unconditionally? | Unconditionally add `CancellationToken`; guard `spawn_background_tasks` call with the flag | Future embedded integrations and users benefit from graceful shutdown regardless; conditional logic would be harder to test and reason about |\n| 2 | Should `validate_ailoop_path` be a generalised `validate_mount_path` reused for both MCP and ailoop? | No: keep them as separate functions | The ailoop path has an additional `/api` restriction not applicable to MCP; merging them would add a parameter and obscure the rule difference. Three similar functions is better than a premature abstraction. |\n| 3 | Should `ensure_no_ailoop_path_collision` accept `mcp_path_if_active: Option<&str>` or call `ensure_no_route_collision` internally? | Separate function with `Option<&str>` for the cross-flag check | Makes the cross-flag collision an explicit argument visible at the call site; easier to unit-test both cases independently |\n| 4 | Should the ailoop base path default to `/ailoop` or something else? | `/ailoop` | Does not collide with any current `NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES`; distinct from `/mcp`; consistent with the raw spec suggestion |\n| 5 | Should `ailoop-server` be gated behind a Cargo feature flag on `crates/cli`? | No; always compiled when the crate is present | MCP serving is not feature-gated; consistency. Operators who want smaller binaries can use `default-features = false` on ailoop-server features instead |\n| 6 | Should the new flags appear in `test_command_metadata.rs`? | Yes, if that test enforces flag parity; update it | Keeps the metadata test as the authoritative surface-area record, consistent with existing practice for `--with-mcp` / `--mcp-path` |\n\n---\n\n## 16. Out of scope (explicit)\n\n- Changes to `newton run`, `newton batch`, or any command other than `newton serve`.\n- Changes to the upstream `ailoop-server` crate (tracked in `goailoop/ailoop#59`).\n- Changes to `ailoop-core` or the HIL operator's WebSocket client.\n- Embedding ailoop-server into `newton mcp serve` or `newton webhook serve`.\n- Multi-instance or multi-prefix ailoop embedding.\n- Authentication or CORS configuration for the embedded ailoop router beyond what `ailoop-server::ServeConfig` provides.\n- Changes to the `NEWTON_AILOOP_*` configuration key names or precedence rules (documented in `crates/core/src/integrations/ailoop/config.rs`).\n- WebSocket smoke tests (listed as optional in acceptance criteria; excluded from required scope).\n- Telegram or other optional ailoop-server features.\n- Changes to `newton run` or `newton batch` to auto-detect and connect to the embedded ailoop.\n\n---\n\n## 17. References\n\n| Symbol / file | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/args.rs:373–394` | Current `ServeArgs` struct to extend |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1663–1678` | `NEWTON_REST_ROUTE_PREFIXES` constant — must be kept in sync with collision check |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1680–1720` | `validate_mcp_path` and `ensure_no_route_collision` — template for new validation functions |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1723–1766` | `serve_mcp_validation_tests` — unit test module to replicate for ailoop |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1769–1903` | `serve()` function — primary modification site |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1842–1855` | MCP router merge block — template for ailoop router merge |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1874–1890` | `mcp_serve_started` structured log — template for `ailoop_serve_started` |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/commands.rs:1893` | `axum::serve` call — replace with `with_graceful_shutdown` form |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/framework_setup.rs:70–81` | `error_codes` module — add `NEWTON_SERVE_AIL_001..004` |\n| `crates/cli/src/cli/mcp.rs` | Pattern for structured startup event and probe-bind |\n| `crates/core/src/integrations/ailoop/config.rs` | `AiloopConfig`, `init_context_for_command_name` — config precedence the operator must update |\n| `crates/cli/tests/integration/serve_with_mcp_responds.rs` | Integration test pattern to replicate for embedded ailoop health test |\n| `Cargo.toml:21` | `ailoop-core` git dependency — same git URL and similar pinning pattern for `ailoop-server` |\n| `goailoop/ailoop#59` | Upstream blocking issue: ailoop-server Axum 0.8 upgrade |","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton/issues/351/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gonewton/newton/issues/351/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135/events","html_url":"https://github.com/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135","id":4222540982,"node_id":"I_kwDOM0DT_M77rty2","number":1135,"title":"Query: replace `serde_urlencoded` with `serde_html_form`","user":{"login":"0x676e67","id":51810656,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUxODEwNjU2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/51810656?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67","html_url":"https://github.com/0x676e67","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/0x676e67/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":7977250816,"node_id":"LA_kwDOM0DT_M8AAAAB23swAA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/labels/dependencies","name":"dependencies","color":"0366d6","default":false,"description":"Pull requests that update a dependency file"},{"id":8776242323,"node_id":"LA_kwDOM0DT_M8AAAACCxrUkw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/labels/E-easy","name":"E-easy","color":"3ee567","default":false,"description":"Effort: Easy! Start here :D"},{"id":9080578915,"node_id":"LA_kwDOM0DT_M8AAAACHT6jYw","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/labels/E-pr-welcome","name":"E-pr-welcome","color":"07e303","default":false,"description":"The feature is welcome to be added, instruction should be found in the issue."}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-08T06:24:39Z","updated_at":"2026-04-16T03:46:42Z","closed_at":"2026-04-16T03:46:42Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"Given that `serde_urlencoded` has had little maintenance in the last 4 years, this could be a good occasion to switch.\n\naxum v0.9 will switch to [`serde_html_form`](https://crates.io/crates/serde_html_form) (see https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/commit/cae6bc37097ea61fcdf94167297072e0e86f9bb6).","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/0x676e67/wreq/issues/1135/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752/events","html_url":"https://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752","id":4425481714,"node_id":"I_kwDOFi7l3s8AAAABB8d98g","number":3752,"title":"Router path compile-time check","user":{"login":"Gabgobie","id":105999094,"node_id":"U_kgDOBlFq9g","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/105999094?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie","html_url":"https://github.com/Gabgobie","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Gabgobie/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":3217112766,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwzMjE3MTEyNzY2","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/labels/T-docs","name":"T-docs","color":"bfd4f2","default":false,"description":"Topic: documentation"},{"id":3548183885,"node_id":"LA_kwDOFi7l3s7TfP1N","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/labels/A-axum","name":"A-axum","color":"ffdc1c","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-05-12T01:28:35Z","updated_at":"2026-05-17T08:51:07Z","closed_at":"2026-05-17T08:51:07Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"- [x] I have looked for existing issues (including closed) about this\n\n## Feature Request\n\n### Motivation\n\nI just had an application compile fine, only to immediately crash on boot. It gave me the error message that \"Paths must start with a `/`\". A reasonable limitation - I was careless. That said, the path was a string literal in this case and should in a perfect world be checked at compile time.\n\n<details><summary>Context</summary>\n\nThe goal was to include dependency attribution on a nested router. I was unsure if the nested router needed a leading slash or if that would cause axum to consider this an absolute path instead of a nested one. Without reading the docs - again the crash is on me and this is early dev - I just tried it out, expecting the compile to fail if this was incorrect. Unfortunately, it failed at runtime instead.\n\n<details><summary><code>attribution.rs</code></summary>\n\n```Rust\nuse axum::{Router, http::{HeaderValue, StatusCode, header}, body::Body, response::Response, routing::get};\n\npub fn router() -> Router {\n    Router::new()\n        .route(\"Cargo.lock\", get(dependencies)) // Note the missing slash\n}\n\nasync fn dependencies() -> Response {\n    const CARGO_LOCK: &str = include_str!(\"../../../Cargo.lock\");\n\n    let mut res = Response::new(Body::from(CARGO_LOCK));\n    *res.status_mut() = StatusCode::OK;\n    res.headers_mut().insert(header::CONTENT_TYPE, HeaderValue::from_static(\"application/toml\"));\n\n    res\n}\n```\n\n</details>\n\n</details>\n\n### Proposal\n\n<!--\nHow should the new feature be implemented, and why? Add any considered\ndrawbacks.\n-->\n\nAt first I just accepted this as a design limitation but then came across http's `HeaderValue::from_static` while trying to figure out the failure modes of `Response::builder` and if it was okay to `.expect` it in my scenario.\n\nI made the flawed assumption that the `const fn from_static` would be executed and panic at compile time but testing it revealed that that's a runtime error (panic in this case) as well. Maybe I misunderstood <https://oneuptime.com/blog/post/2026-01-30-rust-compile-time-constants/view#string-processing-in-const-fn> [^1]\n\nMy last idea would be to use a macro that does the check. The error appears to be produced by the `validate_path` function in `/axum/src/routing/path_router.rs`\n\nhttps://github.com/tokio-rs/axum/blob/c853e44ffce77b771069b6df6bd5adc1b78f1b2f/axum/src/routing/path_router.rs#L22-L34\n\nI'm guessing this is not as easy as just switching this out for a macro due to the need to support dynamic paths but perhaps something can be done to catch errors earlier.\n\n### Alternatives\n\n<!--\nAre there other ways to solve this problem that you've considered? What are\ntheir potential drawbacks? Why was the proposed solution chosen over these\nalternatives?\n-->\n\nBe explicit about this in the docstring of `Router::route`, which currently only lists duplicate routes and empty routes under `Panics`. While the examples don't show any routes that don't start with a `/`, none of them are nested so the original confusion about absolute or relative path remains.\n\nCheers!\n\nEdit: Another consideration may be to have a type that serializes to a correct path string and has a compile-time constructor as well as a runtime one. Or skip the type and provide a `static_route` method that is compile-time checked.\n\n[^1]: Anyways, at this point I spent too much time looking around for possible solutions to just delete this.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/tokio-rs/axum/issues/3752/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/issues/39","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/issues/39/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/issues/39/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/issues/39/events","html_url":"https://github.com/goaikit/aikit/issues/39","id":4452072786,"node_id":"I_kwDOSQRAes8AAAABCV09Ug","number":39,"title":"feat: aikit serve — HTTP server for multi-turn agent sessions","user":{"login":"aroff","id":4482374,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ0ODIzNzQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/4482374?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff","html_url":"https://github.com/aroff","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/aroff/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10824728704,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSQRAes8AAAAChTRAgA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"a2eeef","default":true,"description":"New feature or request"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-15T07:18:27Z","updated_at":"2026-05-17T11:18:20Z","closed_at":"2026-05-17T11:18:20Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"---\nissue: 39\nbranch: feature/39-feat-aikit-serve-http-server-for-multi-turn-agent-sessions\nboard_item_id: PVTI_lADODuD_rs4BRFnwzgs00t4\nsource: github-project\n---\n\n# Feature Spec #39 — `aikit serve`: HTTP Server for Multi-Turn Agent Sessions\n\n**Status:** Implementation-ready enriched spec  \n**Crate:** `aikit-cli` v0.1.111 (Rust, Cargo workspace at `github.com/goaikit/aikit`)  \n**Prerequisite:** Issue #36 (universal `--resume` / session infrastructure) — **confirmed merged** (session_store.rs is present in `aikit-sdk/src/session_store.rs`; `RunOptions::with_session_id` is implemented in `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:232`)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Problem Statement\n\n`aikit agent run` is a one-shot, synchronous CLI call: it reads a prompt from stdin or `--prompt`, invokes the agent, and exits. There is no mechanism for application code to drive a **multi-turn** conversation — sending a follow-up message to the same agent context, receiving a streaming response, then sending another — without managing the CLI process and session files directly. Developers who embed aikit agents into applications (web apps, CI orchestrators, IDE extensions) must build their own process management layer, pipe protocols, and session routing.\n\n`aikit serve` closes this gap by starting a persistent HTTP server that exposes a session-based, SSE-streaming API over any registered agent. The server manages session lifecycle (create, resume, close), enforces concurrency limits, and streams agent events in real time using the W3C EventSource format.\n\n**Out of scope for this spec:** LLM provider authentication management, per-user rate limiting beyond `--max-sessions`, WebSocket transport, persistent server process management (systemd/launchd units), and any changes to the `aikit-sdk` runner or session-store internals beyond consuming existing public APIs.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Goals\n\n1. A new top-level command `aikit serve` is available after this implementation; `aikit serve --help` lists all flags with defaults.\n2. The server exposes a documented HTTP API at a configurable `host:port`; all 7 routes described in this spec MUST be reachable immediately after startup.\n3. Multiple concurrent agent sessions MUST be supported up to the `--max-sessions` cap; sessions are isolated in memory with independent status tracking.\n4. Agent responses MUST be streamed to clients in real time via W3C-compliant SSE (`text/event-stream`); clients MUST receive incremental output without waiting for the full response.\n5. Optional bearer-token authentication MUST be enforced on all requests when `--api-key` is set (via flag or `AIKIT_SERVE_API_KEY` env var).\n6. The server MUST shut down gracefully on SIGTERM/SIGINT, draining in-flight SSE streams before exiting.\n7. All 15 acceptance criteria in §7 MUST be verified by automated tests; agent execution MUST be stubbed in CI to avoid LLM credentials.\n8. No existing CLI commands, tests, or SDK public APIs are broken by this change.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Current Behavior\n\n### Component inventory\n\n| Component | File | Role | Mutable at runtime? |\n|-----------|------|------|---------------------|\n| `build_app()` | `src/cli/mod.rs:32` | Registers all CLI commands with `cli-framework`; dispatches to handlers | No — static registration at startup |\n| `cmd_run()` / `run::execute()` | `src/cli/mod.rs:564`, `src/cli/run.rs:68` | One-shot agent execution; reads prompt from stdin or `--prompt`; blocks until agent exits | No — single-threaded, synchronous |\n| `SessionStore` | `aikit-sdk/src/session_store.rs:47` | Persists `SessionFile` JSON to `~/.aikit/sessions/<id>.json`; supports `load`, `save`, `list`, `update_index` | Yes — per-call file I/O |\n| `RunOptions` | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:121` | Builder struct for agent execution parameters (model, yolo, stream, timeout, session_id, etc.) | No — immutable value passed to runner |\n| `run_agent_events()` | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:2216` | Spawns agent process, reads stdout line-by-line, calls `FnMut(AgentEvent)` callback per event, returns `RunResult` | No — synchronous, blocking |\n| `AgentEvent` | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:528` | Struct: `agent_key`, `seq`, stream source, `AgentEventPayload` | N/A |\n| `AgentEventPayload` | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:448` | Enum: `StreamMessage`, `JsonLine`, `RawLine`, `TokenUsageLine`, `QuotaExceeded`, `RawTransportLine`, … | N/A |\n| `load_persisted_registry()` | `src/core/agent_definition.rs` | Loads agent definitions from `~/.aikit/agents/` and project-level files; returns `SessionRegistry` | No — reads disk on each call |\n\n### Current run and resume flow (summary)\n\n`aikit agent run` reads `--agent` and `--prompt` (or stdin), optionally calls `load_persisted_registry()` to resolve session-agent definitions, builds a `RunOptions` with the resolved session ID (`--resume` / `--resume-last`), then calls `tokio::task::spawn_blocking(run::execute)` because `run_agent_events` is synchronous and cannot run inside a Tokio runtime without `spawn_blocking`. Session state is written to disk by the SDK layer at `~/.aikit/sessions/`. There is no HTTP interface; each invocation is an independent OS process.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Design\n\n### 4.1 Overall architecture\n\n`aikit serve` starts a Tokio-powered `axum` HTTP server. The server holds a single `AppState` instance (wrapped in `Arc`) shared across all request handlers. All session state lives in `AppState.sessions` (an in-memory `HashMap` behind a `Mutex`). The on-disk `SessionStore` (`~/.aikit/sessions/`) continues to be written by `run_agent_events` via the existing SDK session-persistence path, providing resume capability across server restarts.\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  axum Router (tokio async)                                               │\n│                                                                          │\n│  GET /health            ──► health_handler                               │\n│  GET /v1/agents         ──► agents_handler  (load_persisted_registry)    │\n│  POST /v1/sessions      ──► create_session_handler                       │\n│  GET /v1/sessions       ──► list_sessions_handler                        │\n│  GET /v1/sessions/:id   ──► get_session_handler                          │\n│  DELETE /v1/sessions/:id ─► delete_session_handler                       │\n│  POST /v1/sessions/:id/messages ─► messages_handler                     │\n│            │                                                             │\n│            │  spawn_blocking ─► run_agent_events(...)                    │\n│            │         │                   │                               │\n│            │  mpsc::channel           AgentEvent callbacks               │\n│            │         │                   │                               │\n│            └── SSE Sse(ReceiverStream) ◄─┘                               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                │\n                └── AppState { Arc<Mutex<HashMap<session_id, Session>>> }\n```\n\n### 4.2 Data structures\n\n```rust\n/// Top-level shared state passed via axum::extract::State.\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct AppState {\n    sessions: Arc<Mutex<HashMap<String, Session>>>,\n    workdir: PathBuf,      // CWD at server startup; used for load_persisted_registry\n    config: ServeConfig,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct ServeConfig {\n    host: String,                   // default: \"127.0.0.1\"\n    port: u16,                      // default: 8787\n    run_timeout_secs: u64,          // default: 300\n    max_sessions: usize,            // default: 10\n    api_key: Option<String>,        // from --api-key or AIKIT_SERVE_API_KEY\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct Session {\n    session_id: String,\n    agent: String,\n    model: Option<String>,\n    yolo: bool,\n    status: SessionStatus,\n    created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    last_active_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    messages: Vec<SessionMessage>,\n    /// Per-session abort handle; set when a run is in-flight; cleared on completion or cancellation.\n    abort_handle: Option<tokio::task::AbortHandle>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone, PartialEq)]\nenum SessionStatus {\n    Idle,\n    Running,\n    Closed,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone, Serialize)]\nstruct SessionMessage {\n    role: String,          // \"user\" | \"assistant\"\n    content: String,\n    timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n}\n```\n\n**Storage type rationale:** `Arc<Mutex<HashMap<String, Session>>>` is chosen over `DashMap` or `RwLock` because:\n- The critical section is short (session lookup + status flip); lock contention is expected to be minimal.\n- `Mutex` is simpler to reason about under the borrow checker than `RwLock` with interior mutability.\n- The in-memory map is the only runtime store; the SDK-layer `SessionStore` handles disk persistence independently.\n\n**Session identity:** Session IDs are UUID v4 strings generated with the `uuid` crate (`uuid::Uuid::new_v4().to_string()`). They are opaque to the server; the SDK uses the same string as the file stem in `~/.aikit/sessions/<id>.json`.\n\n### 4.3 Concurrency and locking strategy\n\n- The `Mutex` on `AppState.sessions` is held **only for reads/writes to the HashMap** (status transitions, session insertion, session lookup). It MUST NOT be held across `await` points or across `spawn_blocking` calls.\n- The pattern for all handlers:\n  1. Lock the mutex → read/mutate in-memory session state → unlock immediately.\n  2. Pass cloned data (session_id, agent, model, yolo) to `spawn_blocking` by value.\n  3. After the blocking task completes, lock the mutex again to update `status` and `messages`.\n- `spawn_blocking` is used for `run_agent_events` for the same reason `cmd_run` uses it: `run_agent_events` is synchronous and creates its own runtime context internally; running it directly inside an async Tokio task would panic with \"cannot start a runtime from within a runtime\" (see `src/cli/mod.rs:684`).\n- Per-session cancellation uses `tokio::task::JoinHandle::abort()`. The `abort_handle: Option<tokio::task::AbortHandle>` field in `Session` stores the handle. On `DELETE /v1/sessions/:id` or client disconnect, the abort handle is called if present.\n\n### 4.4 SSE streaming\n\nThe messaging handler opens an `axum::response::sse::Sse` response backed by a `tokio::sync::mpsc` channel. The `spawn_blocking` task writes `SseEvent` values into the sender; the Sse extractor drives the receiver as a `Stream`.\n\n**AgentEvent → SSE frame mapping:**\n\n| `AgentEventPayload` variant | SSE event name | SSE data JSON |\n|-----------------------------|----------------|---------------|\n| `StreamMessage { role: Assistant, kind: Message, phase: Delta\\|Final, text }` | `text` | `{\"content\": \"<text>\"}` |\n| `StreamMessage { role: Tool, kind: ToolOutput, … }` | `tool_result` | `{\"name\": \"<agent_key>\", \"output\": \"<text>\"}` |\n| `JsonLine` containing tool-use fields (agent-specific parsing) | `tool_use` | `{\"name\": \"<tool_name>\", \"input\": <object>}` |\n| `TokenUsageLine` | (suppressed — not forwarded to SSE) | — |\n| `QuotaExceeded` | `error` | `{\"code\": \"quota_exceeded\", \"message\": \"<raw_message>\"}` |\n| `JsonLine` / `RawLine` (other) | (suppressed by default) | — |\n\nAfter `run_agent_events` returns:\n- On `Ok(result)` → emit `event: done\\ndata: {\"exit_code\": <n>, \"turn\": <turn_count>}`.\n- On `Err(RunError::TimedOut)` → emit `event: error\\ndata: {\"code\":\"run_timeout\",\"message\":\"Run exceeded timeout\"}` then `event: done` with `exit_code: 1`.\n- On `Err(RunError::AgentNotRunnable(_))` → emit `event: error\\ndata: {\"code\":\"agent_not_runnable\",\"message\":\"<msg>\"}` then `event: done` with `exit_code: 1`.\n- On `Err(RunError::CallbackPanic(_))` or any other `RunError` → emit `event: error\\ndata: {\"code\":\"internal_error\",\"message\":\"Internal error\"}` then `event: done` with `exit_code: 1`. The full error MUST be logged server-side but MUST NOT be included in the SSE data to avoid secret leakage.\n\n**SSE response headers (MUST be set):**\n```\nContent-Type: text/event-stream\nCache-Control: no-cache\nX-Accel-Buffering: no\n```\n\n### 4.5 Authentication middleware\n\nWhen `ServeConfig.api_key` is `Some(key)`, an axum `from_fn` middleware layer intercepts every request and checks `Authorization: Bearer <key>`. Mismatches return HTTP 401 with a JSON error body (see §5). When `api_key` is `None`, the middleware is not installed (zero overhead for unauthenticated deployments).\n\n### 4.6 Startup and shutdown invariants\n\n- The server MUST log `Listening on http://<host>:<port>` to stderr on successful bind.\n- If `host != \"127.0.0.1\"` and `host != \"::1\"`, the server MUST log `Warning: server is bound to a non-loopback address. Set --api-key or restrict access via network ACLs.` to stderr.\n- If the port is already in use, the server MUST exit with a non-zero status and a human-readable error message (`\"error: address already in use: <host>:<port>\"`).\n- On SIGTERM or SIGINT, the server MUST signal all in-flight `spawn_blocking` tasks via their abort handles, wait up to 5 seconds for them to complete, then exit. Remaining tasks are dropped.\n- `workdir` is captured from `std::env::current_dir()` at command startup and is immutable for the server's lifetime.\n\n### 4.7 Session lifecycle visibility rules\n\n- `GET /v1/sessions` returns only sessions with `status != Closed`.\n- `GET /v1/sessions/:id` returns 404 if `status == Closed` or if the ID is not in the map.\n- A session transitions: `Idle → Running` (on message send) → `Idle` (on completion or client disconnect) → `Closed` (on DELETE).\n- `Closed` is terminal; a closed session can never be reopened.\n- `turn_count` in list/get responses equals `session.messages.len() / 2` (each turn adds one user + one assistant message).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Schema and API\n\n### 5.1 CLI types\n\n```rust\n// src/cli/serve.rs\n\npub struct ServeArgs {\n    pub host: String,              // CLI: --host, default: \"127.0.0.1\"\n    pub port: u16,                 // CLI: --port, default: 8787\n    pub run_timeout_secs: u64,     // CLI: --run-timeout-secs, default: 300\n    pub max_sessions: usize,       // CLI: --max-sessions, default: 10\n    pub api_key: Option<String>,   // CLI: --api-key or env AIKIT_SERVE_API_KEY\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 AppState and session types\n\n```rust\n// src/cli/serve.rs\n\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct AppState {\n    sessions: Arc<Mutex<HashMap<String, Session>>>,\n    workdir: PathBuf,\n    config: ServeConfig,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct ServeConfig {\n    host: String,\n    port: u16,\n    run_timeout_secs: u64,\n    max_sessions: usize,\n    api_key: Option<String>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone)]\nstruct Session {\n    session_id: String,\n    agent: String,\n    model: Option<String>,\n    yolo: bool,\n    status: SessionStatus,\n    created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    last_active_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    messages: Vec<SessionMessage>,\n    abort_handle: Option<tokio::task::AbortHandle>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Clone, PartialEq, Serialize)]\n#[serde(rename_all = \"lowercase\")]\nenum SessionStatus { Idle, Running, Closed }\n\n#[derive(Clone, Serialize)]\nstruct SessionMessage {\n    role: String,\n    content: String,\n    timestamp: DateTime<Utc>,\n}\n```\n\n### 5.3 HTTP request/response body types\n\n```rust\n// src/cli/serve.rs — serde types for HTTP bodies\n\n// POST /v1/sessions request\n#[derive(Deserialize)]\nstruct CreateSessionRequest {\n    agent: String,\n    model: Option<String>,\n    #[serde(default)]\n    yolo: bool,\n}\n\n// POST /v1/sessions response (201)\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct CreateSessionResponse {\n    session_id: String,\n    agent: String,\n    model: Option<String>,\n    status: SessionStatus,\n    created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n}\n\n// GET /v1/sessions response (200)\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct ListSessionsResponse {\n    sessions: Vec<SessionSummary>,\n}\n\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct SessionSummary {\n    session_id: String,\n    agent: String,\n    status: SessionStatus,\n    created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    last_active_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    turn_count: usize,\n}\n\n// GET /v1/sessions/:id response (200)\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct GetSessionResponse {\n    session_id: String,\n    agent: String,\n    status: SessionStatus,\n    created_at: DateTime<Utc>,\n    turn_count: usize,\n    messages: Vec<SessionMessage>,\n}\n\n// DELETE /v1/sessions/:id response (200)\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct DeleteSessionResponse {\n    session_id: String,\n    status: SessionStatus,  // always \"closed\"\n}\n\n// POST /v1/sessions/:id/messages request\n#[derive(Deserialize)]\nstruct SendMessageRequest {\n    content: String,\n}\n\n// SSE done event payload\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct SseDonePayload {\n    exit_code: i32,\n    turn: usize,\n}\n\n// SSE error event payload\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct SseErrorPayload {\n    code: String,\n    message: String,\n}\n\n// Error envelope (all non-2xx non-streaming responses)\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct ErrorResponse {\n    error: ErrorDetail,\n}\n\n#[derive(Serialize)]\nstruct ErrorDetail {\n    code: String,\n    message: String,\n}\n```\n\n### 5.4 Handler signatures\n\n```rust\n// src/cli/serve.rs\n\nasync fn health_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n) -> impl IntoResponse;\n\nasync fn agents_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n) -> impl IntoResponse;\n\nasync fn create_session_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n    Json(body): Json<CreateSessionRequest>,\n) -> impl IntoResponse;\n\nasync fn list_sessions_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n) -> impl IntoResponse;\n\nasync fn get_session_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n    Path(session_id): Path<String>,\n) -> impl IntoResponse;\n\nasync fn delete_session_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n    Path(session_id): Path<String>,\n) -> impl IntoResponse;\n\nasync fn messages_handler(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n    Path(session_id): Path<String>,\n    Json(body): Json<SendMessageRequest>,\n) -> Sse<impl Stream<Item = Result<Event, Infallible>>>;\n\n// Auth middleware\nasync fn auth_middleware(\n    State(state): State<AppState>,\n    request: Request,\n    next: Next,\n) -> Response;\n```\n\n### 5.5 Router construction\n\n```rust\n// src/cli/serve.rs\n\nfn build_router(state: AppState) -> Router {\n    let mut router = Router::new()\n        .route(\"/health\", get(health_handler))\n        .route(\"/v1/agents\", get(agents_handler))\n        .route(\"/v1/sessions\", post(create_session_handler))\n        .route(\"/v1/sessions\", get(list_sessions_handler))\n        .route(\"/v1/sessions/:session_id\", get(get_session_handler))\n        .route(\"/v1/sessions/:session_id\", delete(delete_session_handler))\n        .route(\"/v1/sessions/:session_id/messages\", post(messages_handler))\n        .with_state(state.clone());\n\n    if state.config.api_key.is_some() {\n        router = router.layer(from_fn_with_state(state, auth_middleware));\n    }\n    router\n}\n```\n\n### 5.6 Command registration in `src/cli/mod.rs`\n\n```rust\n// src/cli/mod.rs — add to build_app() after cmd_agents_deprecated()\n\nmod serve;\n\n// inside build_app():\nbuilder = builder.register_command(cmd_serve())?;\n\nfn cmd_serve() -> Command {\n    Command {\n        id: \"serve\",\n        summary: \"Start an HTTP server exposing a session-based agent API\",\n        syntax: Some(\"serve\"),\n        category: Some(\"agents\"),\n        spec: Some(Arc::new(CommandSpec {\n            summary: \"Start HTTP server for multi-turn agent sessions (SSE streaming)\",\n            args: vec![\n                opt(\"host\", \"Bind address (default: 127.0.0.1)\"),\n                // port: ArgKind::Option, value_type: ArgValueType::String (parsed to u16)\n                opt(\"port\", \"Port to listen on (default: 8787)\"),\n                opt(\"run-timeout-secs\", \"Cancel agent runs exceeding N seconds (default: 300)\"),\n                opt(\"max-sessions\", \"Max concurrent sessions (default: 10)\"),\n                opt(\"api-key\", \"Require Authorization: Bearer <key>. Also reads AIKIT_SERVE_API_KEY.\"),\n            ],\n            ..CommandSpec::default()\n        })),\n        validator: None,\n        expose_mcp: false,\n        execute: Arc::new(|_ctx, args| {\n            Box::pin(async move {\n                let serve_args = serve::ServeArgs {\n                    host: get_str(&args, \"host\", \"127.0.0.1\"),\n                    port: get_str(&args, \"port\", \"8787\")\n                        .parse::<u16>()\n                        .map_err(|_| anyhow::anyhow!(\"--port must be a valid port number\"))?,\n                    run_timeout_secs: get_str(&args, \"run-timeout-secs\", \"300\")\n                        .parse::<u64>()\n                        .map_err(|_| anyhow::anyhow!(\"--run-timeout-secs must be a positive integer\"))?,\n                    max_sessions: get_str(&args, \"max-sessions\", \"10\")\n                        .parse::<usize>()\n                        .map_err(|_| anyhow::anyhow!(\"--max-sessions must be a positive integer\"))?,\n                    api_key: get_opt(&args, \"api-key\")\n                        .or_else(|| std::env::var(\"AIKIT_SERVE_API_KEY\").ok()),\n                };\n                serve::execute(serve_args).await.map_err(|e| anyhow::anyhow!(\"{}\", e))\n            })\n        }),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 6. Error Codes\n\nAll non-2xx non-streaming responses MUST use the envelope:\n```json\n{ \"error\": { \"code\": \"snake_case_code\", \"message\": \"Human-readable description\" } }\n```\n\n| HTTP Status | Code | Category | Trigger |\n|-------------|------|----------|---------|\n| 400 | `invalid_request` | Client error | `content` field missing or empty in `POST /v1/sessions/:id/messages`; malformed JSON body |\n| 401 | `unauthorized` | Auth | `Authorization: Bearer` header absent or token does not match configured `api_key` |\n| 404 | `session_not_found` | Client error | Session ID does not exist in the in-memory map, or session status is `Closed` |\n| 404 | `not_found` | Client error | Route not matched by the router (fallback handler) |\n| 409 | `session_busy` | Concurrency | `POST /v1/sessions/:id/messages` sent while session status is `Running` |\n| 422 | `invalid_request` | Client error | `agent` field missing in `POST /v1/sessions`; `content` is present but empty string |\n| 429 | `session_limit_reached` | Capacity | `POST /v1/sessions` attempted while `sessions.len() >= max_sessions` (counting non-Closed) |\n| 500 | `internal_error` | Server error | Unhandled panic or unexpected error; full error MUST be logged server-side, MUST NOT appear in response body |\n| 504 | `run_timeout` | Timeout | Emitted as an SSE `event: error` frame (not as an HTTP status) when `run_agent_events` returns `RunError::TimedOut`; followed immediately by `event: done` with `exit_code: 1` |\n\n> **Note on 504:** Because the SSE stream is already open when the timeout occurs, it is delivered as an `event: error` SSE frame rather than an HTTP 504 response. HTTP 504 SHOULD NOT be used as a pre-flight error for this endpoint.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. `aikit serve --help` prints help text listing `--host`, `--port`, `--run-timeout-secs`, `--max-sessions`, `--api-key`, each with its default value.\n2. `GET /health` returns HTTP 200 with body `{\"status\":\"ok\",\"version\":\"<semver>\"}` where `<semver>` matches the value of `env!(\"CARGO_PKG_VERSION\")` at build time.\n3. `GET /v1/agents` returns HTTP 200 with `{\"agents\":[...]}` containing one entry per registered agent definition. When no agents are defined, `{\"agents\":[]}` is returned (not 404 or 500).\n4. `POST /v1/sessions` with a valid `{\"agent\":\"<name>\"}` body returns HTTP 201 with a JSON body containing a `session_id` field whose value is a valid UUID v4 string.\n5. A `GET /v1/sessions/{id}` on the session ID from criterion 4 returns HTTP 200 with `status: \"idle\"`.\n6. `GET /v1/sessions` returns a JSON object with a `sessions` array containing all non-Closed sessions; a freshly created session appears in the array.\n7. `POST /v1/sessions/{id}/messages` with `{\"content\":\"<prompt>\"}` returns a `text/event-stream` response; the stream MUST contain at least one SSE frame, MUST end with an `event: done` frame whose data contains `exit_code` and `turn` fields, and MUST close cleanly.\n8. A second `POST /v1/sessions/{id}/messages` sent while the first is still streaming returns HTTP 409 with `{\"error\":{\"code\":\"session_busy\",\"message\":\"...\"}}`.\n9. After `event: done` is received on a message stream, `GET /v1/sessions/{id}` MUST return `status: \"idle\"`.\n10. `DELETE /v1/sessions/{id}` returns HTTP 200 with `{\"session_id\":\"...\",\"status\":\"closed\"}`; a subsequent `GET /v1/sessions/{id}` returns HTTP 404.\n11. `POST /v1/sessions` when `max_sessions` sessions are already active (non-Closed) returns HTTP 429 with `{\"error\":{\"code\":\"session_limit_reached\",\"message\":\"Maximum of N concurrent sessions reached\"}}` where N equals `--max-sessions`.\n12. With `--api-key mysecret` set: a request with `Authorization: Bearer wrongkey` returns HTTP 401 with `{\"error\":{\"code\":\"unauthorized\",\"message\":\"...\"}}`. A request with `Authorization: Bearer mysecret` succeeds.\n13. Starting the server with `--host 0.0.0.0` logs a security warning containing \"non-loopback\" to stderr.\n14. A run that exceeds `--run-timeout-secs` emits an SSE `event: error` frame with `\"code\":\"run_timeout\"` followed by an `event: done` frame with `exit_code: 1`. After the stream closes, `GET /v1/sessions/{id}` returns `status: \"idle\"` (not `running`).\n15. When an HTTP client disconnects mid-stream, a subsequent `GET /v1/sessions/{id}` returns `status: \"idle\"` (the session recovers from the abandoned run).\n16. On receipt of SIGTERM, in-flight SSE streams complete (or are drained within 5 seconds); the process exits with status 0.\n17. An integration test starts the server on `127.0.0.1:0` (OS-assigned port), exercises `/health`, `GET /v1/agents`, `POST /v1/sessions`, `POST /v1/sessions/{id}/messages`, `DELETE /v1/sessions/{id}`. Agent execution MUST be stubbed (mock `run_agent_events`) so no LLM credentials are needed in CI.\n18. All existing CLI commands (`aikit check`, `aikit init`, `aikit install`, `aikit update`, `aikit remove`, `aikit list`, `aikit release`, `aikit agent run`, `aikit agent list`, `aikit agent check`, `aikit agent mcp list`, `aikit agent mcp add`, `aikit package init`, `aikit package validate`, `aikit package build`, `aikit package publish`) and all existing tests pass without modification.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Functionality Comparison (Before vs. After)\n\n| Capability | Before (v0.1.111) | After |\n|------------|-------------------|-------|\n| Multi-turn agent conversations from code | Not possible; each `aikit agent run` is a new process | Yes — sessions persist across `POST /v1/sessions/:id/messages` calls |\n| Streaming agent output to a remote client | Not possible; streaming only to local stdout | Yes — W3C SSE stream delivered over HTTP |\n| Concurrent agent sessions | Not supported; sequential one-shot CLI calls only | Yes — up to `--max-sessions` concurrent sessions |\n| Agent discovery via HTTP | Not available | `GET /v1/agents` returns registered agents |\n| Session lifecycle management | Only via `--resume` / `--resume-last` on CLI | Full CRUD: create, list, inspect, delete via REST |\n| Authentication | N/A (CLI process) | Optional bearer-token auth via `--api-key` |\n| Graceful shutdown | N/A | Drains in-flight SSE streams on SIGTERM/SIGINT |\n| Session status visibility | Terminal output only | `GET /v1/sessions/:id` returns `idle`/`running`/`closed` |\n| CI-safe server tests | N/A | Integration tests stub `run_agent_events` |\n\n---\n\n## 9. Benefit of Implementing This Functionality\n\n`aikit serve` transforms aikit from a developer tool into an embeddable backend service. The primary beneficiaries:\n\n- **Application developers** building web UIs, CI orchestrators, or IDE extensions can drive agent conversations with a simple HTTP client — no process management, no pipe protocols, no session file parsing.\n- **The aikit ecosystem** gains a standard integration point: any language or framework that can make HTTP requests and consume SSE can now use aikit agents.\n- **Operational teams** benefit from session observability (`GET /v1/sessions`) and optional authentication without deploying additional proxy infrastructure.\n\nThe value compounds with issue #36's session infrastructure: the server is thin (it delegates state to the existing SDK session layer) and is therefore low-risk to implement and maintain.\n\n---\n\n## 10. Stages\n\n### Stage 1 — CLI scaffolding (no networking)\n\n**Deliverable:** `aikit serve --help` works; `ServeArgs` is parsed correctly; the execute function resolves args and logs startup info but does not yet bind a port.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Create `src/cli/serve.rs` with `ServeArgs`, `ServeConfig`, `execute()` stub that logs `\"Starting server on <host>:<port>\"` and returns `Ok(())`.\n- Add `mod serve;` to `src/cli/mod.rs`.\n- Add `cmd_serve()` function to `src/cli/mod.rs` and register it in `build_app()`.\n- Add `axum = { version = \"0.8\", features = [\"macros\"] }`, `tokio-stream = \"0.1\"`, and `uuid = { version = \"1\", features = [\"v4\"] }` to `Cargo.toml [dependencies]`.\n- Confirm `cargo build` succeeds.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** None.\n\n### Stage 2 — Server startup, router skeleton, and health endpoint\n\n**Deliverable:** Server binds to `host:port`, responds to `GET /health`, logs startup message, and handles port-in-use error.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Implement `AppState` and `Session` structs in `src/cli/serve.rs`.\n- Implement `build_router()` function.\n- Implement `health_handler()` returning `{\"status\":\"ok\",\"version\":\"<version>\"}`.\n- Implement 404 fallback handler for unknown routes (`{\"error\":{\"code\":\"not_found\",\"message\":\"Not Found\"}}`).\n- Implement startup logic in `execute()`: bind `TcpListener`, log startup message, log non-loopback warning, run `axum::serve` with graceful shutdown on SIGTERM/SIGINT.\n- Add port-in-use error handling with clear message.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 1 (Cargo deps must compile).\n\n### Stage 3 — Authentication middleware\n\n**Deliverable:** With `--api-key` set, all requests (including `/health`) require `Authorization: Bearer <key>`; without `--api-key`, no auth is enforced.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Implement `auth_middleware` as `axum::middleware::from_fn_with_state`.\n- Conditionally layer it in `build_router()` only when `api_key.is_some()`.\n- Acceptance criterion 12 can now be verified manually.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 2 (router must exist).\n\n### Stage 4 — Session CRUD endpoints\n\n**Deliverable:** Sessions can be created, listed, inspected, and deleted via HTTP; all 5 non-messaging endpoints are functional.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Implement `create_session_handler` (POST /v1/sessions): validate `agent` present; check `max_sessions`; generate UUID v4; insert `Session`; return 201.\n- Implement `list_sessions_handler` (GET /v1/sessions): return non-Closed sessions with `turn_count`.\n- Implement `get_session_handler` (GET /v1/sessions/:id): return session detail + message history; 404 if Closed or absent.\n- Implement `delete_session_handler` (DELETE /v1/sessions/:id): transition to Closed; abort in-flight run via `abort_handle`; 404 if already Closed or absent.\n- Implement `agents_handler` (GET /v1/agents): call `load_persisted_registry(&state.workdir)`; serialize to JSON matching `aikit agent list --json` shape; 500 on load failure.\n- Add `ErrorResponse` / `ErrorDetail` types with `IntoResponse` impl.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 3 (auth middleware).\n\n### Stage 5 — Messaging endpoint (SSE streaming)\n\n**Deliverable:** `POST /v1/sessions/:id/messages` streams agent output as SSE, with full pre-flight validation, timeout, and client-disconnect handling.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Implement `messages_handler`:\n  - Pre-flight checks: session not found/closed (404), session busy (409), empty content (422).\n  - Status transition: `Idle → Running`, append user message.\n  - Build `RunOptions` from session fields (model, yolo, session_id, timeout via `Duration::from_secs(run_timeout_secs)`).\n  - Create `tokio::sync::mpsc::channel` for SSE event delivery.\n  - `spawn_blocking` the `run_agent_events` call; capture the `JoinHandle` and store its `abort_handle` in the session.\n  - Map `AgentEventPayload` variants to SSE frames per §4.4.\n  - Emit `event: done` on completion.\n  - After stream end: transition session `Running → Idle`; append assistant message; update `last_active_at`; clear `abort_handle`.\n  - On client disconnect: abort the blocking task; transition session `Running → Idle`.\n  - Timeout handling: use `RunOptions::with_timeout(Duration::from_secs(run_timeout_secs))`; on `RunError::TimedOut`, emit error + done frames.\n- Set SSE response headers (`Content-Type: text/event-stream`, `Cache-Control: no-cache`, `X-Accel-Buffering: no`).\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 4 (Session state machine must be in place).\n\n### Stage 6 — Tests and integration test harness\n\n**Deliverable:** All 18 acceptance criteria from §7 are covered by automated tests; CI passes without LLM credentials.\n\n**Scope:**\n- Add `tests/serve/` directory with:\n  - `serve_smoke_test.rs`: integration test starting server on `127.0.0.1:0`, exercising `/health`, `GET /v1/agents`, full session lifecycle (create → message → done → delete). Uses a stub/mock for `run_agent_events` that emits a fixed sequence of `AgentEvent` values.\n  - `serve_auth_test.rs`: tests 401 on bad key, 200 on correct key.\n  - `serve_limits_test.rs`: tests 429 on `max_sessions` exceeded, 409 on concurrent message, 422 on empty content.\n  - `serve_timeout_test.rs`: stub that sleeps past `run_timeout_secs`; verifies `run_timeout` SSE error.\n  - `serve_disconnect_test.rs`: drops client connection mid-stream; verifies session returns to `idle`.\n- Add snapshot test `tests/snapshots/aikit_serve.rs` for `aikit serve --help` output.\n\n**Blocking dependency:** Stage 5 (all endpoints must be functional).\n\n---\n\n## 11. Breaking Changes\n\nThis feature is **purely additive**. The following items are explicitly verified to be non-breaking:\n\n| Change | Impact on existing users |\n|--------|--------------------------|\n| New `mod serve` in `src/cli/mod.rs` | None — new module, no changes to existing modules |\n| New `cmd_serve()` registered in `build_app()` | None — adds a new command; all existing commands unchanged |\n| New dependencies: `axum`, `tokio-stream`, `uuid` | Binary size increases. No API or behavior changes. |\n| New feature: `AIKIT_SERVE_API_KEY` env var | None — env var is only read by `cmd_serve()`; other commands ignore it |\n\nThe `aikit-sdk` public API (`run_agent_events`, `RunOptions`, `AgentEvent`, `SessionStore`) is consumed but not modified.\n\n---\n\n## 12. Modified Files and Summary\n\n| File / Path | Summary of Modifications |\n|-------------|--------------------------|\n| `src/cli/mod.rs` | Add `mod serve;` import; add `cmd_serve()` function; call `builder.register_command(cmd_serve())?` inside `build_app()`; no changes to existing command functions |\n| `src/cli/serve.rs` | **New file.** Contains: `ServeArgs`, `ServeConfig`, `AppState`, `Session`, `SessionStatus`, `SessionMessage`; all HTTP handler functions; `build_router()`; `execute()` entry point; auth middleware; SSE event mapping logic; error response types |\n| `Cargo.toml` | Add to `[dependencies]`: `axum = { version = \"0.8\", features = [\"macros\"] }`, `tokio-stream = \"0.1\"`, `uuid = { version = \"1\", features = [\"v4\"] }` |\n| `tests/serve/serve_smoke_test.rs` | **New file.** Integration test: server on port 0, health + agents + full session lifecycle with stubbed `run_agent_events` |\n| `tests/serve/serve_auth_test.rs` | **New file.** Tests 401/200 auth middleware behavior |\n| `tests/serve/serve_limits_test.rs` | **New file.** Tests 429, 409, 422 error codes |\n| `tests/serve/serve_timeout_test.rs` | **New file.** Tests `run_timeout` SSE error with stubbed timeout |\n| `tests/serve/serve_disconnect_test.rs` | **New file.** Tests session recovery after client disconnect |\n| `tests/snapshots/aikit_serve.rs` | **New file.** Snapshot test for `aikit serve --help` output |\n\n**Existing tests** in `tests/integration/commands.rs`, `tests/cli_integration_test.rs`, `tests/run_events_cli.rs`, and all `tests/snapshots/` MUST pass unchanged (criterion 18).\n\n---\n\n## 13. Dependencies\n\n### New external crate dependencies (all blocking Stage 1)\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose | If skipped |\n|------------|---------|---------|------------|\n| `axum` | `0.8` with `macros` feature | HTTP server framework, SSE support, routing | Cannot implement serve without it |\n| `tokio-stream` | `0.1` | Convert mpsc receiver to `Stream` for axum SSE | Required for `ReceiverStream`; no alternative without custom impl |\n| `uuid` | `1` with `v4` feature | Generate UUID v4 session IDs | Could use timestamp+random alternative, but uuid is idiomatic |\n\n**Note on `hyper`/`tower` duplication:** `reqwest 0.12` (already in `Cargo.toml:28`) uses `hyper 1.x` internally. `axum 0.8` also requires `hyper 1.x`. They share the same `hyper`/`tower` stack — no duplicate transitive deps expected. Verify with `cargo tree -d` after adding deps.\n\n### Existing dependencies (already present, required by serve)\n\n| Dependency | Location | Used for |\n|------------|----------|---------|\n| `tokio = { version = \"1\", features = [\"full\"] }` | `Cargo.toml:44` | Async runtime, `spawn_blocking`, channels |\n| `chrono = { version = \"0.4\", features = [\"serde\"] }` | `Cargo.toml:68` | `DateTime<Utc>` in session types |\n| `serde / serde_json` | `Cargo.toml:35-36` | JSON serialization of all HTTP bodies |\n| `tracing / tracing-subscriber` | `Cargo.toml:74-75` | Structured logging from handlers |\n| `anyhow` | `Cargo.toml:39` | Error propagation in `execute()` |\n| `aikit-sdk` (path dep) | `Cargo.toml:56` | `run_agent_events`, `RunOptions`, `AgentEvent`, `load_persisted_registry` (via `src/core/agent_definition`) |\n\n### Internal dependencies (non-blocking unless otherwise noted)\n\n| Internal dependency | Required by | Blocking stage | Status |\n|--------------------|-------------|---------------|--------|\n| Issue #36 session infrastructure | `RunOptions::with_session_id` | All stages | **Merged** — `aikit-sdk/src/session_store.rs` and `runner.rs:232` confirmed present |\n| `src/core/agent_definition::load_persisted_registry` | `GET /v1/agents` handler | Stage 4 | Present — used by `src/cli/agents.rs:14` |\n\n---\n\n## 14. Proposed Folder Structure\n\nOnly new and modified paths are listed; the remainder of the project is unchanged.\n\n```\naikit/\n├── Cargo.toml                          # MODIFIED: add axum, tokio-stream, uuid deps\n├── src/\n│   └── cli/\n│       ├── mod.rs                      # MODIFIED: register cmd_serve\n│       └── serve.rs                    # NEW: full serve implementation (~600–900 LOC)\n└── tests/\n    ├── serve/\n    │   ├── serve_smoke_test.rs         # NEW\n    │   ├── serve_auth_test.rs          # NEW\n    │   ├── serve_limits_test.rs        # NEW\n    │   ├── serve_timeout_test.rs       # NEW\n    │   └── serve_disconnect_test.rs    # NEW\n    └── snapshots/\n        └── aikit_serve.rs              # NEW: --help snapshot\n```\n\n---\n\n## 15. Design Decisions\n\n| # | Question | Decision | Rationale |\n|---|----------|----------|-----------|\n| 1 | Top-level `aikit serve` vs. `aikit agent serve`? | Top-level (`aikit serve`) | Accepted criteria require `aikit serve --help`. The serve command manages infrastructure, not just agent execution; placing it at top level (alongside `aikit check`, `aikit init`) is consistent with its infrastructure role. |\n| 2 | `axum` vs. `warp` vs. `actix-web` vs. `hyper` directly? | `axum 0.8` | axum shares `hyper 1.x` with `reqwest 0.12` already in the tree (no dup), has first-class SSE support, integrates cleanly with tokio, and has stable ergonomics for extractors and middleware. |\n| 3 | Add deps to `[workspace.dependencies]` vs. root `[dependencies]` directly? | Add directly to root `[dependencies]` (do NOT create `[workspace.dependencies]`) | Only the root `aikit-cli` crate needs these deps. `[workspace.dependencies]` adds complexity without benefit when only one member uses the dependency. |\n| 4 | `std::sync::Mutex` vs. `tokio::sync::Mutex` vs. `RwLock` for sessions map? | `std::sync::Mutex` | The critical section is short (HashMap read/write); it is never held across await points. `std::sync::Mutex` is simpler and avoids async-poisoning concerns. |\n| 5 | In-memory session state vs. persisting `Session` struct to disk? | In-memory only; SDK session store handles disk persistence | The `Session` struct contains server-lifecycle fields (status, abort_handle) that have no meaning across restarts. The SDK's `SessionFile` handles the conversation state needed for LLM resume. Duplicating that to another format adds sync complexity. |\n| 6 | CancellationToken placement: `AppState` (spec prose) vs. `Session` (type definition)? | Per-`Session` `abort_handle: Option<AbortHandle>` | The spec prose says \"held in AppState\" but the type definition omits it. Per-session handles are strictly necessary for per-session cancellation and are the natural Tokio pattern. `AppState` should not hold per-session handles. |\n| 7 | Validate agent existence at `POST /v1/sessions` or on first message? | On first message (as specified) | Keeps session creation fast; avoids I/O at session-creation time; consistent with the spec's stated rationale. |\n| 8 | UUID v4 for session IDs vs. other ID schemes? | UUID v4 via `uuid` crate | Globally unique without coordination; collision probability is negligible; widely understood; easy to parse and log. |\n| 9 | Graceful shutdown timeout? | 5 seconds drain window | Balances responsiveness (not hanging indefinitely) with completeness (most LLM responses complete well under 5s). Configurable in a future spec. |\n| 10 | How to stub `run_agent_events` in tests? | Inject a test-mode function pointer or use a trait object in `AppState` | The concrete approach (trait vs. function pointer) is an implementation choice left to the implementer; the requirement is that CI tests MUST NOT require LLM credentials. |\n\n---\n\n## 16. Out of Scope (Explicit)\n\n- **LLM provider authentication:** The server does not manage API keys for claude/codex/gemini/etc. Those credentials are already resolved by the SDK layer from environment variables.\n- **Per-user or per-session rate limiting:** Only the global `--max-sessions` cap is implemented. Per-client or per-IP request rate limiting is out of scope.\n- **WebSocket transport:** Only SSE (W3C EventSource) is supported. WebSocket support is a separate feature.\n- **TLS/HTTPS termination:** The server binds HTTP only. TLS must be handled by a reverse proxy (nginx, caddy, etc.).\n- **Persistent server process management** (systemd units, launchd plists, Docker entrypoints): Out of scope.\n- **Changes to `aikit-sdk` public API:** `run_agent_events`, `RunOptions`, `AgentEvent`, `SessionStore` are consumed but not modified.\n- **Changes to on-disk session format** (`~/.aikit/sessions/`): The `SessionFile` schema is unchanged.\n- **`aikit agent serve` alias:** The command is registered as `aikit serve` only; no deprecated alias under `aikit agent serve`.\n- **Hot-reload of agent definitions:** The server calls `load_persisted_registry()` per `GET /v1/agents` request; it does not watch the filesystem for changes.\n- **Admin/metrics endpoints** (e.g., `/metrics`, `/v1/admin`): Out of scope.\n- **Session expiry / TTL-based cleanup:** Sessions remain in memory until explicitly deleted or the server restarts. Idle session expiry is out of scope.\n- **Multi-file splitting of `serve.rs`** into sub-modules: The implementation MAY fit in a single file; splitting is at the implementer's discretion, not required by this spec.\n\n---\n\n## 17. References\n\n**Entry points to start implementation from:**\n\n| Symbol / File | Location | Relevance |\n|---------------|----------|-----------|\n| `build_app()` | `src/cli/mod.rs:32` | Register `cmd_serve()` here, following the same pattern as `cmd_check()` (line 42) |\n| `cmd_run()` and its `execute` closure | `src/cli/mod.rs:564`, `src/cli/run.rs:68` | `spawn_blocking` pattern for synchronous SDK calls inside tokio async; copy this pattern for the messages handler |\n| `run_agent_events()` signature | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:2216` | `pub fn run_agent_events<F>(agent_key: &str, prompt: &str, options: RunOptions, mut on_event: F) -> Result<RunResult, RunError> where F: FnMut(AgentEvent) + Send` |\n| `RunOptions` builder | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:172` | `RunOptions::new().with_session_id(…).with_stream(…).with_yolo(…).with_timeout(…)` |\n| `AgentEvent` struct | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:528` | `agent_key: String`, `seq: u64`, plus payload field |\n| `AgentEventPayload` enum | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:448` | `StreamMessage`, `JsonLine`, `RawLine`, `TokenUsageLine`, `QuotaExceeded`, `RawTransportLine` variants |\n| `StreamMessage` struct | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:434` | `text`, `phase` (Delta/Final), `role` (Assistant/Tool/System/User), `kind` (Message/Reasoning/ToolOutput/Status) |\n| `RunError` variants | `aikit-sdk/src/runner.rs:370–377` | `TimedOut`, `AgentNotRunnable`, `CallbackPanic`, `QuotaExceeded`, `WrongAgentKey`, `SessionNotFound` |\n| `SessionStore` | `aikit-sdk/src/session_store.rs:47` | Disk persistence; `SessionFile`, `SessionTurn` types |\n| `load_persisted_registry()` | `src/core/agent_definition.rs` | Called by `agents_handler`; same call as `src/cli/agents.rs:14` |\n| `DefinitionRecord` JSON shape | `src/cli/agents.rs:113–128` | Exact JSON fields for `GET /v1/agents` response (name, description, source, model, tools, disallowedTools, agents, path) |\n| Existing integration test pattern | `tests/integration/commands.rs:1` | Pattern for `Command::new(\"aikit\").arg(…).output()` tests |\n| `Cargo.toml [dependencies]` | `Cargo.toml:23` | Add `axum`, `tokio-stream`, `uuid` here |","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/issues/39/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/goaikit/aikit/issues/39/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29/events","html_url":"https://github.com/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29","id":4432802478,"node_id":"I_kwDOPU_VVM8AAAABCDcyrg","number":29,"title":"[FEATURE] Wire up TlsConfig for TLS termination and mTLS client certs","user":{"login":"edenreich","id":16985712,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjE2OTg1NzEy","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/16985712?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich","html_url":"https://github.com/edenreich","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/edenreich/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":9024768209,"node_id":"LA_kwDOPU_VVM8AAAACGesI0Q","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"a2eeef","default":true,"description":"New feature or request"},{"id":10883694593,"node_id":"LA_kwDOPU_VVM8AAAACiLgAAQ","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/labels/released","name":"released","color":"ededed","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-05-12T21:35:12Z","updated_at":"2026-05-12T22:22:43Z","closed_at":"2026-05-12T22:19:36Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":{"id":25131682,"node_id":"IT_kwDOC6ve6c4Bf3qi","name":"Feature","description":"A request, idea, or new functionality","color":"blue","created_at":"2025-01-20T19:13:54Z","updated_at":"2025-01-20T19:13:54Z","is_enabled":true},"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Summary\n\n`TlsConfig` (`src/config.rs:41-46`) is parsed from `SERVER_TLS_*` env vars in `Config::from_env()` (lines 253-266) but never consumed by the Axum server. As a result, the A2A endpoint cannot terminate TLS and cannot require client certificates, even though the spec allows `MutualTlsSecurityScheme`.\n\n## Current state\n\n- `Config::from_env()` populates `tls_config: Option<TlsConfig>` and `ServerConfig.tls_enable` / `tls_cert_path` / `tls_key_path`, then drops them on the floor.\n- `A2AServer::serve(addr)` binds plain HTTP via Axum — no `axum-server` integration, no `rustls` / `native-tls`, no client-cert extraction.\n- `MutualTlsSecurityScheme` is present in the generated wire types but unreachable from the runtime.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Wire `TlsConfig` through `A2AServer` so `SERVER_TLS_ENABLE=true` + cert/key paths actually terminate TLS.\n- [ ] Optional but desirable: support requiring a client certificate (mTLS) when an `AgentCard` skill advertises `MutualTlsSecurityScheme` — extract the peer certificate subject and plumb it through as an authenticated principal (similar shape to `AuthenticatedPrincipal`).\n- [ ] Pick a TLS stack (most likely `axum-server` + `rustls`); document why in the PR description.\n- [ ] Add an `examples/tls/` scenario showing self-signed cert generation, mTLS handshake from the client, and the server enforcing the client-cert subject as the principal.\n- [ ] Document `SERVER_TLS_*` env vars in the README.\n\n## Context\n\nSpun off from #25 (\"out of scope: mTLS support — the TlsConfig struct is similarly unwired\"). Pairs with #28 for the scheme-dispatch side of mTLS.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/inference-gateway/rust-adk/issues/29/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1","id":4434818828,"node_id":"I_kwDOSb_BS88AAAABCFX3DA","number":1,"title":"[Epic] Rust MCP server 初期実装","user":{"login":"yhonda-ohishi","id":87104778,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjg3MTA0Nzc4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/87104778?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi","html_url":"https://github.com/yhonda-ohishi","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/yhonda-ohishi/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":10938082034,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSb_BS88AAAACi_Xi8g","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/labels/epic","name":"epic","color":"ededed","default":false,"description":null},{"id":10938082037,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSb_BS88AAAACi_Xi9Q","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/labels/mcp","name":"mcp","color":"ededed","default":false,"description":null},{"id":10938082040,"node_id":"LA_kwDOSb_BS88AAAACi_Xi-A","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/labels/rust","name":"rust","color":"ededed","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"closed","locked":true,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":1,"created_at":"2026-05-13T04:31:10Z","updated_at":"2026-05-15T22:39:55Z","closed_at":"2026-05-15T22:39:55Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## 概要\n\nGitHub API を叩く MCP server を Rust で実装。auth-worker (`ippoan/auth-worker`) の MCP OAuth Provider と連携し、Device Authorization Grant (RFC 8628) で認証する。\n\n## ゴール\n\n- stdio transport で Claude Code / Claude Desktop から接続可能\n- auth-worker 経由で Device Flow 認証\n- GitHub Issues / PRs の read/write tool を提供\n- GitHub Releases で複数プラットフォーム binary 配布\n\n## 関連リポジトリ\n\n- このRepo: `ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs` (Rust)\n- Auth 側: `ippoan/auth-worker` ([Epic #91](https://github.com/ippoan/auth-worker/issues/91))\n- Project board: https://github.com/orgs/ippoan/projects/3\n\n## 技術スタック\n\n- Rust + Axum + rmcp (or rust-mcp-sdk)\n- octocrab (GitHub API client)\n- tokio (async runtime)\n- reqwest (HTTP client for auth-worker)\n- jsonwebtoken (JWT 検証)\n\n## サブIssue\n\n(作成後にここを更新)\n\n- [ ] リポジトリ初期化 (Cargo workspace, README, LICENSE, CI)\n- [ ] Phase 4: Device Flow client (token cache + polling)\n- [ ] Phase 4: MCP server skeleton (rmcp + stdio)\n- [ ] Phase 5: GitHub API 統合 (octocrab + introspect)\n- [ ] Phase 5: list_issues tool 実装\n- [ ] Phase 8: GitHub Actions release workflow\n\n## 決定事項 (2026-05-13)\n\n| 項目 | 値 |\n|------|-----|\n| Rust binary メモリキャッシュ TTL | 1時間 |\n| 401時のキャッシュ無効化 + 1回 retry | 必須 |\n| キャッシュの永続化 | しない (プロセス終了で消える) |\n| Transport | stdio のみ (初期)、HTTP は将来検討 |\n\n## 参考\n\n- [RFC 8628](https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc8628)\n- [rmcp - Rust MCP SDK](https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/rust-sdk)\n- [Auth flow 設計 (auth-worker側 Epic)](https://github.com/ippoan/auth-worker/issues/91)","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ippoan/github-mcp-server-rs/issues/1/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39/events","html_url":"https://github.com/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39","id":4507254189,"node_id":"I_kwDOSX-sDM8AAAABDKc9rQ","number":39,"title":"browse: migrate browser ↔ server API to Protocol Buffers + ConnectRPC","user":{"login":"wadackel","id":5393238,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjUzOTMyMzg=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/5393238?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel","html_url":"https://github.com/wadackel","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/wadackel/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-05-23T07:08:02Z","updated_at":"2026-05-23T16:00:46Z","closed_at":"2026-05-23T16:00:46Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"OWNER","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"# `browse`: migrate browser ↔ server API to Protocol Buffers + ConnectRPC\n\n## Summary\n\nReplace the current handwritten REST/JSON API between the `browse` SPA and the Rust server with a Protocol Buffers schema served over [ConnectRPC](https://connectrpc.com/). The single `.proto` definition becomes the source of truth for request/response types, and both the Rust handlers and the TypeScript client are generated from it. The existing JSON endpoints are removed in a single hard cut (no dual-transport window).\n\n## Motivation\n\nThe `browse` HTTP surface currently has eight handlers in [`src/cli/render/browse.rs`](src/cli/render/browse.rs) (lines 439–479 for the router), each with a manually maintained Rust response struct (`#[derive(Serialize)]`) and a mirroring TypeScript type in [`web/src/lib/types.ts`](web/src/lib/types.ts). Adding a field requires editing the Rust struct, the TS interface, and the fetch helper in `web/src/lib/api.ts` separately; nothing prevents the two sides from drifting.\n\nGoals:\n\n1. **Single source of truth.** One `.proto` file defines every request/response shape; Rust and TypeScript types are generated, not handwritten.\n2. **End-to-end type safety and client generation.** The browser-side client is generated from the schema, so endpoint names, parameter names, and response fields are checked at TS compile time.\n\nNon-goals (see [Out of scope](#out-of-scope)) include performance optimisation and multi-client support — they may follow later but are not what this change is for.\n\n## Current state\n\n| Aspect | Today |\n|---|---|\n| Server framework | `axum` 0.8 on a single-threaded tokio runtime, bound to `127.0.0.1` |\n| Frontend | React 19 + Vite SPA, embedded via `rust-embed` from `web/dist/` |\n| Transport | HTTP/1.1, JSON bodies, parameters via query string only (workflow IDs contain `/`) |\n| Schema definition | Manual: Rust structs in `src/cli/render/browse.rs`, mirrored TS types in `web/src/lib/types.ts` |\n| Codegen | None |\n| Tests | `tests/e2e_browse.rs` spawns the binary and asserts on raw HTTP responses |\n\nEndpoints in scope (all unary, see `build_router` at `src/cli/render/browse.rs:439`):\n\n- `GET /api/graph` → `GraphPayload`\n- `GET /api/repo` → `RepoInfo` (or 404)\n- `GET /api/triggers` → `TriggersResponse`\n- `GET /api/search?q&kind&limit` → `SearchResponse`\n- `GET /api/event-impact?event` → `EventImpactResponse`\n- `GET /api/node?kind&id` → `NodeResponse`\n- `GET /api/impact?id` → `ImpactResponse`\n- `GET /api/trace?id` → `TraceResponse`\n\n## Proposal\n\n### Schema layout\n\n```\nproto/\n└── ravelact/\n    └── browse/\n        └── v1/\n            └── browse.proto\n```\n\nDefine a single service `ravelact.browse.v1.BrowseService` with one unary RPC per existing endpoint:\n\n- `GetGraph`, `GetRepo`, `ListTriggers`, `Search`, `GetEventImpact`, `GetNode`, `GetImpact`, `Trace`\n\n`TraceJsonNode` (currently a discriminated union of 8 variants in TS) maps to a protobuf `oneof`.\n\n### Toolchain\n\n| Concern | Choice |\n|---|---|\n| Rust runtime | [`connectrpc`](https://crates.io/crates/connectrpc) crate v0.6+ (Anthropic's official Tower-based implementation) with the `axum` feature |\n| Rust message types | `buffa` + `buffa-types` (required by `connectrpc`; zero-copy alternative to `prost`) |\n| Rust codegen | `connectrpc-build` invoked from `build.rs`, with `protoc-gen-connect-rust` and `protoc-gen-buffa` |\n| TypeScript codegen | `@bufbuild/protoc-gen-es` + `@connectrpc/connect-web` |\n| Schema tooling | [`buf`](https://buf.build/product/cli) for lint, format, and breaking-change checks |\n| Default wire format | **JSON over Connect** for the browser (DevTools-debuggable; binary remains available per-request) |\n| Streaming | Not used; all RPCs are unary |\n| Error model | Connect's structured errors (`Code` + `message` + optional `details`) |\n\n> **Verification required during implementation.** The `connectrpc` crate is pre-1.0 (v0.6 as of this writing). Confirm the API surface and `buffa` version pins are still current when the work starts.\n\n### Generated code policy\n\n**Generated code is checked into the repository**, not produced at Nix build time. Rationale: the `browse` Nix build is already complicated by the `web/dist/` requirement (see `docs/development.md`); pulling `buf` + `protoc` + the codegen plugins into the Nix sandbox would compound that. With vendored generated code:\n\n- `nix build .#default` continues to work without protobuf tooling.\n- The Nix `devShell` includes `buf` and the codegen plugins for development.\n- CI runs codegen and `git diff --exit-code` to catch drift between `.proto` and generated files.\n\nGenerated code locations:\n\n- Rust: `src/cli/render/browse/proto/` (new module)\n- TypeScript: `web/src/proto/`\n\nBoth directories carry a `// @generated` header and are excluded from formatters/linters.\n\n### Migration approach\n\nHard cut, in one PR (or a stacked PR set merged together):\n\n1. Add `proto/`, `buf.yaml`, `buf.gen.yaml`, codegen scripts (`just proto-gen` etc.), and the generated files.\n2. Replace the eight axum handlers in `src/cli/render/browse.rs` with ConnectRPC service implementations mounted under the existing axum `Router`.\n3. Replace `web/src/lib/api.ts` and `web/src/lib/types.ts` with ConnectRPC client calls against the generated stubs.\n4. Rewrite `tests/e2e_browse.rs` to drive the server through a ConnectRPC client (over HTTP/1.1, JSON encoding) instead of raw TCP — the snapshot assertions update accordingly.\n5. Delete the obsolete handwritten types and JSON serialisation code.\n\nThe existing JSON endpoints are removed in the same change; there is no `/api/v2/*` parallel surface.\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n- All eight `/api/*` endpoints.\n- Both server and client.\n- E2E test rewrite (`tests/e2e_browse.rs`).\n- `just` recipes for `proto-gen`, `proto-lint`, `proto-check-drift`.\n- CI job that runs codegen and fails on drift.\n- `docs/development.md` updates for the new dev loop.\n\n### Out of scope\n\n- Performance benchmarking (binary protobuf vs JSON wire size, etc.).\n- Adding streaming RPCs — all calls remain unary.\n- Exposing `browse` to remote / multi-user clients.\n- Re-enabling the `browse` Nix build (tracked separately; see `docs/development.md`).\n- Migrating any non-`browse` interfaces (e.g., the CLI's other subcommands, IR cache format).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] `proto/ravelact/browse/v1/browse.proto` defines `BrowseService` with the eight RPCs listed above; `buf lint` passes.\n- [ ] Rust server compiles with the generated stubs and serves all eight RPCs via ConnectRPC mounted on the existing axum router.\n- [ ] The React SPA uses the generated TS client exclusively; no `fetch(\"/api/...\")` calls remain in `web/src/`.\n- [ ] No `#[derive(Serialize)]` response structs remain in `src/cli/render/browse.rs` for the eight endpoints (the handwritten types are gone, not just unused).\n- [ ] No JSON-only `/api/*` route handlers remain.\n- [ ] `tests/e2e_browse.rs` drives the server through the generated client and passes (`nix develop -c just test`).\n- [ ] `nix develop -c just format lint test lint-actions` is green.\n- [ ] CI fails when `.proto` is changed without re-running codegen (drift check).\n- [ ] `web/dist/` still gets embedded by `rust-embed`; `cargo run --release -- --root . browse` opens the SPA and every panel works end-to-end (graph load, search, node detail, impact, trace, event impact, triggers, repo info).\n- [ ] `docs/development.md` documents the new dev loop including the codegen step.\n\n## Implementation plan (high level)\n\n1. **Schema first.** Land `proto/`, `buf.yaml`, `buf.gen.yaml`, `just proto-gen`, and the generated Rust + TS directories — both as committed files — so subsequent steps have stable type imports.\n2. **Server.** Swap each handler to its ConnectRPC equivalent, one or two at a time within the PR, so review can compare old vs new field-by-field. The router still owns asset serving for `rust-embed`.\n3. **Client.** Replace `web/src/lib/api.ts` and `web/src/lib/types.ts` with imports from `web/src/proto/`. Update call sites.\n4. **Tests.** Rewrite `tests/e2e_browse.rs` against a generated Connect client; refresh `insta` snapshots once.\n5. **Cleanup.** Delete dead code, JSON serialisation, and obsolete TS types.\n6. **CI.** Add the drift-check job and a `buf lint` step.\n\nEach step should keep `nix develop -c just format lint test lint-actions` green.\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\n- **`connectrpc` crate stability.** v0.6 is pre-1.0 and the README notes the API surface \"may shift in 0.x\". Pin exact versions; revisit if the API breaks before this work merges. Confirm the conformance-suite claim by running their reference tests once during implementation.\n- **`buffa` is non-standard.** Most Rust protobuf code uses `prost`; `buffa` is part of the `connectrpc` stack and zero-copy. Generated types will differ from typical `prost`-style ergonomics — worth a short note in `docs/development.md` so contributors know why.\n- **`oneof` for `TraceJsonNode`.** The 8-variant TS discriminated union maps to a protobuf `oneof`. Verify the generated TS shape is ergonomic before committing to the schema; if the codegen output is awkward, consider splitting into separate response message types per variant.\n- **Snapshot test churn.** `tests/e2e_browse.rs` snapshots will change because the serialiser changes (Connect-JSON encoding may differ trivially from current `serde_json` output — e.g., default-value omission, integer formatting). Plan to review every snapshot diff explicitly during the test-rewrite step; do not blanket-accept.\n- **Browser HTTP/2 vs HTTP/1.1.** Connect-over-HTTP/1.1 is sufficient and matches the current axum setup. No TLS / HTTP/2 work is implied.\n\n## References\n\n- ConnectRPC protocol spec: <https://connectrpc.com/docs/protocol/>\n- `connectrpc` crate (Rust): <https://crates.io/crates/connectrpc>\n- `anthropics/connect-rust` (Rust runtime + codegen): <https://github.com/anthropics/connect-rust>\n- `@connectrpc/connect-web` (TypeScript client): <https://github.com/connectrpc/connect-es>\n- `buf` CLI: <https://buf.build/docs/cli>\n- Current handlers: `src/cli/render/browse.rs:439-479`\n- Current TS types: `web/src/lib/types.ts`\n- Current dev-loop notes: `docs/development.md`\n\n---\n\n### Assumptions (please correct on review)\n\n- Deliverable type and detail level were inferred from the request as \"GitHub Issue, implementation-level\".\n- Service / package naming follows `ravelact.browse.v1.*` — change if the project has a different convention for future RPC namespaces.\n- The eight endpoints listed above are the complete set; no additional `browse` endpoints are planned in the same PR.\n- The `browse` PoC remains single-user / `127.0.0.1`-only after this change.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/wadackel/ravelact/issues/39/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uBlockOrigin/uAssets/issues/32863","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uBlockOrigin/uAssets","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uBlockOrigin/uAssets/issues/32863/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uBlockOrigin/uAssets/issues/32863/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/uBlockOrigin/uAssets/issues/32863/events","html_url":"https://github.com/uBlockOrigin/uAssets/issues/32863","id":4403987442,"node_id":"I_kwDOA0q3Wc8AAAABBn-D8g","number":32863,"title":"kodular.io: breakage","user":{"login":"Unknown78","id":25132599,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI1MTMyNTk5","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/25132599?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78","html_url":"https://github.com/Unknown78","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Unknown78/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false