rsion = \"0.12\", features = [\"json\"] }\ntracing = \"0.1\"\ntracing-subscriber = \"0.3\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## PHI LOOP (mandatory)\n```\nedit spec -> seal hash -> gen -> test -> verdict -> experience -> skill commit -> git commit\n```\n\n---\n\n## LAWS\n\n- **L1**: NO `.sh` files\n- **L2**: PR must close this issue with `Closes #N`\n- **L3**: `cargo clippy -- -D warnings` zero warnings\n- **L4**: `cargo test` all tests pass. New code = new tests\n- **L5**: trios-server stays port `9005`. trios-mcp browser server = port `3025`\n- **L6**: Graceful `Err` returns, no panics\n- **L7**: Write to `.trinity/experience/`\n- **L8**: Every file change = immediate commit + push\n\n---\n\n## Integration\n\nAdd to root `Cargo.toml` workspace:\n```toml\nmembers = [\n  # ... existing ...\n  \"crates/trios-mcp\",\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n## DONE checklist\n\n- [ ] `crates/trios-mcp/` exists in repo (L8 verified on GitHub)\n- [ ] `cargo build -p trios-mcp` succeeds\n- [ ] `cargo clippy -p trios-mcp -- -D warnings` = 0 warnings (L3)\n- [ ] `cargo test -p trios-mcp` all pass (L4)\n- [ ] Axum server starts on port 3025\n- [ ] WebSocket `/ws` accepts Chrome Extension connections\n- [ ] Lighthouse audit returns structured JSON\n- [ ] MCP client connects to upstream MCP server\n- [ ] Root `Cargo.toml` includes `crates/trios-mcp`\n- [ ] Experience log written to `.trinity/experience/` (L7)\n- [ ] PR opened with `Closes #<this>` (L2)\n- [ ] No `.sh` files (L1)\n\n---\n\n## Source reference\n\nOriginal code to port: https://github.com/gHashTag/tri-mcp\n\n- `browser-tools-server/` -> `src/server.rs` + `src/websocket.rs` + `src/lighthouse.rs`\n- `browser-tools-mcp/mcp-server.ts` -> `src/mcp_client.rs`\n- `chrome-extension/` -> vendor as-is, no rewrite\n\nGenerал армии агентов ждет рапорта. Удачи, солдат.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/gHashTag/trios/issues/259/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"htt