"body":"> Part of epic #28 · **Blocked by:** #1, #2 · **Blocks:** #6, #7, #10\n\n## Goal\n\nServe the `marketplace.json` Claude Code consumes, plus expose internally-authored plugins as **dumb-HTTP git repos** so Claude Code's clone step (`/plugin install`) works against skill-pool directly.\n\n## Success criteria\n\n- [ ] `GET https://<tenant>.skill-pool.example.com/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` returns valid JSON matching Claude Code's marketplace schema (`name`, `owner`, `plugins[]`). Each `plugins[].source` resolves to a working git URL.\n- [ ] `GET https://<tenant>.skill-pool.example.com/git/plugins/<slug>.git/info/refs?service=git-upload-pack` returns a valid git-protocol response.\n- [ ] `git clone https://<tenant>.skill-pool.example.com/git/plugins/<slug>.git` succeeds from a shell and yields a tree containing `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` + the bundled skill/agent/command files in the right filesystem layout.\n- [ ] Public read access (no token required) on both endpoints; rate-limited via the existing per-tenant limiter.\n- [ ] The marketplace JSON is regenerated whenever a plugin is published/archived (in-process invalidation, no manual refresh needed).\n\n## Files\n\n- New: `server/src/routes/marketplace.rs` — `/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` handler; assembles JSON from `plugin_marketplace_entries`.\n- New: `server/src/routes/plugin_git.rs` — dumb-HTTP git endpoint. Decide between `git2` in-process vs shelling to `git http-backend` (boss makes the call in the mini-plan).\n- New: `server/src/plugin_git.rs` — helper: take a `PluginManifest` + `PluginContent[]` → materialise the filesystem tree → `git commit` → write to a bare repo at `<storage>/<tenant>/plugins/<slug>.git/`.\n- Update: `server/src/storage.rs` — add `plugin_git_path(tenant_id, slug) -> PathBuf`.\n- Update: `server/src/routes/mod.rs` — wire the two new modules at root paths (not under `/v1/`).\n\n## Tests\n\n- New: `server/tests/marketplace_json.rs` — publish a plugin via the API from #2; assert the tenant's `/.claude-plugin/marketplace.json` lists it with the right `source` URL pointing to skill-pool's own git endpoint.\n- New: `server/tests/plugin_git_clone.rs` — programmatic `git clone` via `git2` against the in-process server; assert the cloned tree contains `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` + the expected skill files.\n- New: `server/tests/marketplace_public_read.rs` — confirm no auth required on `marketplace.json` or git endpoints; confirm rate limit still applies.\n- Smoke: `git clone https://<host>/<tenant>/git/plugins/<slug>.git` from a shell against a running portal.\n\n## Agent team\n\n| Role | Subagent type | Responsibility |\n|---|---|---|\n| Boss | `backend-architect` | Reviews the git-endpoint design (security of serving HTTP git; correctness of pack generation; `git2` vs `git http-backend` trade-off). Signs off on the architectural choice in the mini-plan before workers start. |\n| Worker | `rust-pro` | Implements both routes + the manifest-to-git-tree helper. |\n| Worker | `c-pro` *(only if needed)* | Pulled in if low-level git pack/protocol debugging is required. |\n| Verifier | `test-automator` | Runs the three new tests + the shell-level `git clone` smoke test. |\n\n## Standing protocol — read before starting\n\n1. **Boss** reads this issue + linked files. Posts a 1-page mini-plan as the **first comment** — including the git2-vs-shell decision with justification.\n2. **Workers** execute in parallel; each opens a PR scoped to one sub-task; link the PR here.\n3. **Boss reviews every PR** before merge.\n4. **Verifier** runs the listed tests + the shell smoke test.\n5. **Boss closes** once Verifier signs off AND every Success criterion is checked.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/olafkfreund/skill_pool/issues/31/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/olafkfreund/skill_pool/issues/31/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0}],"search_type":"lexical"}